insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Tools for effective multi-objective optimization using swarm intelligence','<p>Simultaneous optimization of several competing objectives is a hard computational task. In general case (where no simplifying assumptions on the objective functions are given) multi-objective optimization is attacked by algorithms based on (meta)heuristics.</p>\n\n<p>The swarm intelligence methodology has been used for solving multi-objective optimization problems in the last decade. Multi-objective Particle Swarm Optimization (MOPSO) is a stochastic population-based evolutionary algorithm, which searches the objective space of the problem for a set of non-dominated trade-offs corresponding to a set of optimal solutions. Despite the popularity of evolutionary methods for multi-objective optimization (MOO) and swarm intelligence, several questions related to the  practicality of the MOPSO methodology remain open:</p>\n\n<p>1) What is a proper sizing of population and the archive of alternative solutions? Should it be dynamic and why?\n2) What are the appropriate rates for variation of individuals in a swarm?\n3) How to improve exploration of the Pareto frontier in the objective space during a MOPSO run? \n4) What are appropriate selection schemes for archiving successful intermediate solutions?\n5) What are the characteristics of a user-friendly MOPSO tool, which provide a competitive advantage compared to existing optimization routines? (E.g.,  what is the minimal number of parameters that the user has to specify and how to reduce it further? How to represent the obtained solutions to the user to ease the process of interpretation and final selection?)</p>\n\n<p>This project can be performed on various levels by bachelor-, maser-, and PhD students. Optimization using swarm intelligence offers plenty of questions to be answered, and tools to be implemented in a bachelor thesis and also in a master thesis. The directions for algorithm development and software engineering  are adapted to the interests, ambitions, and goals of a student.</p>\n\n<p>Examples of quesitons are the following:</p>\n\n<p>A) Efficient implementation of a robust MOPSO algorithm in C++ and embedding it into a popular scientific environment like MatLab or Mathematica (or Excel??) (taking into account question (5) above).</p>\n\n<p>B) Experimental analysis of the developed algorithm on a set of test problems with respect to questions (1)-(4) above.</p>\n\n<p>C) Analysis of the feasibility of the parallelization of the algorithm and potential necessity for algorithmic modifications  (students interested in Cuda are particularly encouraged to apply).</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Tools for effective multi-criteria optimization using swarm intelligence','<p>Simultaneous optimization of several competing objectives is a hard computational task. In general case (where no simplifying assumptions on the objective functions are given) multi-objective optimization is attacked by algorithms based on (meta)heuristics.</p>\n\n<p>The swarm intelligence methodology has been used for solving multi-objective optimization problems in the last decade. Multi-objective Particle Swarm Optimization (MOPSO) is a stochastic population-based evolutionary algorithm, which searches the objective space of the problem for a set of non-dominated trade-offs corresponding to a set of optimal solutions. Despite the popularity of evolutionary methods for multi-objective optimization (MOO) and swarm intelligence, several questions related to the practicality of the MOPSO methodology remain open:</p>\n\n<p>1) What is a proper sizing of population and the archive of alternative solutions? Should it be dynamic and why? 2) What are the appropriate rates for variation of individuals in a swarm? 3) How to improve exploration of the Pareto frontier in the objective space during a MOPSO run? 4) What are appropriate selection schemes for archiving successful intermediate solutions? 5) What are the characteristics of a user-friendly MOPSO tool, which provide a competitive advantage compared to existing optimization routines? (E.g., what is the minimal number of parameters that the user has to specify and how to reduce it further? How to represent the obtained solutions to the user to ease the process of interpretation and final selection?)</p>\n\n<p>This project can be performed on various levels by bachelor-, maser-, and PhD students. Optimization using swarm intelligence offers plenty of questions to be answered, and tools to be implemented in a bachelor thesis and also in a master thesis. The directions for algorithm development and software engineering are adapted to the interests, ambitions, and goals of a student.</p>\n\n<p>Examples of quesitons are the following:</p>\n\n<p>A) Efficient implementation of a robust MOPSO algorithm in C++ and embedding it into a popular scientific environment like MatLab or Mathematica (or Excel??) (taking into account question (5) above).</p>\n\n<p>B) Experimental analysis of the developed algorithm on a set of test problems with respect to questions (1)-(4) above.</p>\n\n<p>C) Analysis of the feasibility of the parallelization of the algorithm and potential necessity for algorithmic modifications (students interested in Cuda are particularly encouraged to apply).</p>\n\n<p>Key words: modeling, simulation, computational intelligence, software engineering, GPUs, Cuda, swarm behaviour, social systems</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Space-filling designs computed on GPUs','<p>The problem of analysis of given multi-variate input-response data is crucial in applications of computational intelligence related to modeling of measured or simulated data produced by a complex system.  It is preceded by a problem of constructing the multi-variate input-response data through a designed experiment.</p>\n\n<p>A designed experiment for a real or simulation-based system is seeking for a an appropriate design of N points in the d-dimensional space of controllable variables (input space). It then generates N points in a r-dimensional space of control variables (output space), either via running a simulation N times, or via real measurements. </p>\n\n<p>Design of Experiments is concerned with finding such designs (sets of points in the input space), that are maximally space-filling, which usually suggests that maximal distance among point is minimized, or minimal distance is maximized.  The problem of constructing space-filling designs of N points in a space of arbitrary dimensionality $d$ is still open, and most of the optimal designs are unknown. </p>\n\n<p>To generate plausible approximations of space-filling sets (semi-space-filling designs) heuristic algorithms are used. Often a genetic algorithm is run on a set of arbitrarily chosen N points in the d-dimensional space, which optimized the location of point so, that the minimal distance is maximized, or maximal distance is minimized.  The solution of a genetic algorithm depends then on the choice of the initial guess on the location of points. </p>\n\n<p>The first  challenge of this project is to implement an efficient algorithm for creation of semi-space filling designs of arbitrary size in the space of arbitrary dimensionality using computations of GPUs and compare the properties of generated designs with (a few) known optimal designs from www.spacefillingdesigns.nl. The possibility of developing such algorithm is indicated in [1] and encompasses the use of the Simple Multi-dimensional Iterative Techniqes for Subsampling (SMITS), introduced in [1]. </p>\n\n<p>The second challenge of this project is to perform algorithmic modifications to the SMITS procedure in such a way, that the SMITS procedure becomes parallelizable, can be implemented in Cuda, and run on GPUs  for efficient analysis of very large given input-output data sets.</p>\n\n<p>[1] Model-based problem solving with symbolic regression via genetic programming by E.Vladislavleva, ISBN:978 90 5668 217 0</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Efficient tools for effective optimization using swarm intelligence','<p>Efficient optimization of an arbitrary multi-variate function is a hard computational task. Various optimization algorithms were developed within numerical optimization, but they all have the same pitfalls:</p>\n\n<p>1) They are searching for a local minimum, and unless multi-variate function is convex, the globality of the obrained optimum is  hard to guarantee and even harder to confirm;</p>\n\n<p>2) They are all iterative, due to which the result (a local minimum found) often depends on the location of the initial point where the search started.</p>\n\n<p>Evolutionary population-based algorithms are developed as an alternative to the \'classical\' numerical  optimization algorithms.  This project will focus on the application of the swarm intelligence methodology to the task of a single-objective optimization of an arbitrary  function (with many variables) given analytically. The particle swarm optimization strategy simulates a behaviour of animals in a swarm (e.g. a flock of birds or a scull of fish), where the directions of single individuals in a swarm do not only depend on their individual wishes (cognitive component), but also on the global moving direction of the swarm (social component).  </p>\n\n<p>Particle Swarm optimization has been successfuly used for various optimization problems in the last decade, and yet stays a quickly evolving field due to growing complexity of the problems that computational science is daring to solve. </p>\n\n<p>This project will be targeted at an efficient implementation of the robust Particle Swarm Optimization algorithm of high reproducibility. Due to the fact that PSO is a stochastic population-based evolutionary algorithm, it is naturally parallelizable; and one of the tasks of this project is to study the ways for massive parallellisation of a PSO algorithm.</p>\n\n<p>The project can be performed on Bachelor-, Master-, and PhD level. Master students, who have more time for the thesis will be challenged to incorporate particle swarm optimization with other evolutionary algorithms for modeling data. </p>\n\n<p>The directions for every particular project on this topic are changed with respect to the interests and ambitions of a student. The following topics related to both software engineering and research are examples of project directions. </p>\n\n<p>1) Implementation of  an efficent PSO algorithm in C++, turning it into an engine callable from popular scientific environments like MatLab, or Mathematica, and analyzing the competitiveness of the new PSO algorithm compared with the standard embedded routines for function optimization?</p>\n\n<p>2) Development of a robust  PSO algorithm for global optimization, with a built-in functionality for searching for all local minima of the given function?</p>\n\n<p>3) Analysis of the effects of specialisation of particles in a swarm performing the tasks of exploration and exploitation on the reproducibility of the algorithm.</p>\n\n<p>4) Implementation of the PSO algorithm in Cuda for GPU-based computing (or  analysis of the feasibility of such an implementation and potential necessity for algorithmic modifications). Comparisons of Cuda imlementation with the C++ implementation. </p>\n\n<p>Key words: modeling, modelling,  simulation, computational intelligence, software engineering, GPUs, Cuda, swarm behaviour, social systems</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Tools for effective function optimization using swarm intelligence','<p>Efficient optimization of an arbitrary multi-variate function is a hard computational task. Various optimization algorithms were developed within numerical optimization, but they all have the same pitfalls:</p>\n\n<p>1) They are searching for a local minimum, and unless multi-variate function is convex, the globality of the obrained optimum is hard to guarantee and even harder to confirm;</p>\n\n<p>2) They are all iterative, due to which the result (a local minimum found) often depends on the location of the initial point where the search started.</p>\n\n<p>Evolutionary population-based algorithms are developed as an alternative to the \'classical\' numerical optimization algorithms. This project will focus on the application of the swarm intelligence methodology to the task of optimizing an arbitrary function (with many variables) given analytically. </p>\n\n<p>The particle swarm optimization strategy simulates a behaviour of animals in a swarm (e.g. a flock of birds or a scull of fish), where the directions of single individuals in a swarm do not only depend on their individual wishes (cognitive component), but also on the global moving direction of the swarm (social component). Individuals in a virtual swarm are searching for optima of a function with many variables (up to 1000 variables). They swarm in the multi-variate space exploring the function values and move to the next locations with a bias towards two goals: the best value that they have discovered on their own, and the globally best value discovered by the swarm (individuals in the swarm can \'communicate\' with each other to infer knowledge about the best point, that they have jointly seen). </p>\n\n<p>Particle Swarm optimization has been successfuly used for various optimization problems in the last decade, and yet stays a quickly evolving field due to growing complexity of the problems that computational science is daring to solve.</p>\n\n<p>This project will be targeted at an efficient implementation of the robust Particle Swarm Optimization algorithm of high reproducibility. Due to the fact that PSO is a stochastic population-based evolutionary algorithm, it is naturally parallelizable; and one of the tasks of this project is to study the ways for massive parallellisation of a PSO algorithm.</p>\n\n<p>The project can be performed on Bachelor-, Master-, and PhD level. Master students, who have more time for the thesis will be challenged to incorporate particle swarm optimization with other evolutionary algorithms for modeling data.</p>\n\n<p>The directions for every particular project on this topic are changed with respect to the interests and ambitions of a student. The following topics related to both software engineering and research are examples of project directions.</p>\n\n<p>1) Implementation of an efficent PSO algorithm in C++, turning it into an engine callable from popular scientific environments like MatLab, or Mathematica, and analyzing the competitiveness of the new PSO algorithm compared with the standard embedded routines for function optimization.</p>\n\n<p>2) Development of a robust PSO algorithm for global optimization, with a built-in functionality for searching for all local minima of the given function.</p>\n\n<p>3) Analysis of the effects of specialisation of particles in a swarm performing the tasks of exploration and exploitation on the reproducibility of the algorithm. (e.g. what is an optimal ratio of explorers and exploiters in a swarm).</p>\n\n<p>4) Implementation of the PSO algorithm in Cuda for GPU-based computing (or analysis of the feasibility of such an implementation and potential necessity for algorithmic modifications). Comparisons of Cuda imlementation with the C++ implementation.</p>\n\n<p>Key words: modeling, simulation, computational intelligence, software engineering, GPUs, Cuda, swarm behaviour, social systems</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Performance Analysis of WSDM-enabled Web Services','<p>Grote gedistribueerde enterprise software wordt hoe langer hoe meer gestructureerd in de vorm van Service-Oriented Architectures (SOA&rsquo;s), waarbij bestaande softwarecomponenten gewrapt wordt in XML-gebaseerde web services. In feite omvat het SOA-paradigma de best practices van gedistribueerd programmeren van ruwweg de voorbije twintig jaar en commercieel ondersteund door bedrijven blijft SOA in populariteit toenemen.</p>\r\n<p>Het doel van deze thesis is een zo goed mogelijke inschatting te bekomen van het <strong>prestatievermogen van web services (QoS)</strong>. Hiervoor kunnen zowel functionele als niet-functionele aspecten van services beschouwd worden. De <strong><a href=\"http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/webservices/library/ws-wisdom/\">WSDM-specificatie</a></strong> (Web Services Distributed Management) is een OASIS-standaard die vastlegt hoe je zulke eigenschappen zou kunnen meten en observeren. Het <a href=\"http://ws.apache.org/muse/\">Apache MUSE</a> project is een generieke softwarebibliotheek die de gebruiker in staat stelt web services conform deze WSDM-specificatie te ontwikkelen en te hosten op Java applicatieservers zoals Tomcat of Glassfish, of zelfs op mobiele devices m.b.v. technologie&euml;n zoals OSGi.</p>\r\n<p><strong>In deze thesis werk je m.b.v. Apache MUSE aan een implementatie die een goede QoS-estimation oplevert en bestudeer je academische publicaties om gepaste algoritmen in je oplossing te pluggen. Dit valt grotendeels samen met het implementeren van MOWS (Management of Web Services), een beperkt deel van de WSDM-specificatie waarvoor Apache MUSE nog geen implementatie biedt.</strong></p>\r\n<p>Alvorens aan de uitwerking te beginnen zal je begeleid worden om op zeer korte termijn de concepten achter SOA&rsquo;s en web services specificaties (WS-* standaards) te begrijpen. Vervolgens bekijk je de software-architectuur van Apache MUSE, bestudeer je welke parameters nodig zijn om de QoS van services te bepalen en ontwerp je een implementatie.</p>\r\n<p>Een grondig begrip van XML en XML Schema (XSD) is aanbevolen. Toepassen van software design patterns tijdens de implementatie is een pluspunt. Mogelijk kan je een basiskennis putten uit de vakken Gedistribueerde Systemen en/of Distributed Computing Paradigms uit de eerste master.</p>\r\n<p>Voor je verdure carri&egrave;re zal je tijdens de uitwerking van deze thesis in aanraking komen met (open-source) technologie&euml;n zoals Java Enterprise Edition (J2EE), Apache Axis2, Apache MUSE en populaire APIs zoals JAX-WS en JAX-B. Verder zal je een grondige kennis opdoen over SOA&rsquo;s en de WS-* standardisatie-initiatieven van OASIS en W3C. We richten voornamelijk op de J2EE-omgeving, maar als je liever wil experimenteren met mobile devices dan kan door ook in samenspraak met de begeleiders.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'NetBeans plugin for WSDM SOA projects','<p>De <a href=\"http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/webservices/library/ws-wisdom/\">Web Services Distributed Management (WSDM)</a> specificatie vormt een krachtige en flexibele omgeving voor het ontwikkelen van manageable web services met capabilities die het organiseren en herconfigureren van complexe gedistribueerde systemen aanzienlijk kunnen vergemakkelijken voor systeembeheerders.</p>\r\n<p>Het <a href=\"http://ws.apache.org/muse\">Apache MUSE</a> project is een generieke softwarebibliotheek die de gebruiker in staat stelt web services conform deze WSDM-specificatie te ontwikkelen en ze te hosten op Java applicatieservers of op mobiele devices. Maar het ontwikkelproces met Apache MUSE is grotendeels command-line, en sommige van de handige features in <a href=\"http://www.netbeans.org\">NetBeans</a> zijn niet beschikbaar als je het project dan toch importeert als <em>free-form</em> project.</p>\r\n<p><strong>De bedoeling van dit project is een plugin te programmeren voor NetBeans die toelaat op een overzichtelijke wijze een project te kunnen beheren voor het bouwen van WSDM services (en clients)</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Achterliggend zorgt de plugin voor een goede bestandsstructuur in het project en stuurt die de tools van het MUSE project.</li>\r\n<li>Je integreert nieuwe opties in bestaande dialoogvensters en menubalk om diverse gangbare taken (zoals het deployen op een applicatieserver, het toevoegen van capabilities met bijbehorende generatie van skeletton code etc.) op dezelfde manier mogelijk te maken als in andere (standaard) NetBeans projecten</li>\r\n<li>Je maakt een entry in de Library Manager om op een eenvoudige manier de MUSE sources, binaries/JARs en javadocs voor het project beschikbaar te stellen</li>\r\n<li>En je mapt de ingebouwde debuggingfunctionaliteit van NetBeans zodat de client en de service zelf op eenvoudige manier gedebugd kunnen worden.</li>\r\n</ul>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'An adaptive OSGi robotic application');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Context Aware Adaptation Framework with application on Lego Robot','<p>Nowadays, technologies are providing the smart terminals, such as smartphones and robots, with unprecedented powerful computational abilities. However, the context environment of these terminals is frequently changing. In order to improve their performance, it is important to make adaptation corresponding to different changes.<p></p>\n\n<p>We have developed an adaptation framework which combined Aspect Oriented Programming (AOP) with OSGi to provide a flexible way to organize adaptations in heterogeneous environment. We have also tested our adaptation framework to manipulate the adaptation of video displayed by Mplayer.<p></p>\n\n<p><center><img src=\"http://www.win.ua.ac.be/~vincenz/robot.JPG\"></center><br></p>\n\n<p>This thesis will implement the application shown in the above picture. A first step is to create an interface between a Lego MindStorm Robot and our adaptation framework. Sensors in the LEGO Robot could work as monitors, while adaptations could be carried out by controlling the servo motors in the robot. A possible way to achieve this is by Java Programming through the researches carried out in the <a href=\"http://lejos.sourceforge.net\">LEJOS</a> project.<p> </p>\n\n<p>A next will be to further explore the complex adaptation algorithms to guide the adaptations of the robot, and create the connections/interactions between the robot and other applications. <p></p>\n\n<p>Finally, a web service interface shall be used to automatically publish the monitored changes, and possibly use the web service to remotely control the adaptations of the robot. Such experiment could be applied in smart assistive environments where they could have a great impact.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Multicast/Broadcast Transparency in Wireless Mesh Networks','<p>Wishbone is een spin-off activiteit van de PATS onderzoeksgroep die zich focust op de ontwikkeling van Wireless Mesh Networks. Meer informatie over onze activiteiten kan je vinden op http://www.wishbone.be/. Wishbone zelf is een klein team van 3 PATS-leden die zich bezighouden met de ontwikkeling van ons product.</p>\n\n<p>Onze oplossing biedt een L3 mesh netwerk aan dat o.a. kan gebruikt worden als backbone gedeelte voor een access netwerk uit te rollen voor b.v. events en hard-to-wire places. Sommige toepassingen vereisen echter dat het mesh netwerk volledig transparant is voor de data die er over gaat. Dit is nu reeds het geval voor unicast verkeer en wij willen dit uitbreiden naar multicast en broadcast toepassingen.</p>\n\n<p>Wij zoeken in het kader van de onderzoeksstage een gemotiveerde student die genteresseerd is om zich te verdiepen in deze problematiek, vervolgens een werkend proof-of-concept op te zetten met onze hardware. Indien er voldoende tijd beschikbaar is zou het de bedoeling zijn deze proof-of-concept samen met ons verder uit te werken naar ons productiesysteem.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Service Redundancy in Wireless Mesh Networks','<p>De PATS onderzoeksgroep is reeds een aantal jaren actief bezig met onderzoek in het domein van draadloze netwerken. Onze focus hierbij ligt meestal op de ontwikkeling en performantie evaluatie van MAC en routerings protocols voor dit soort netwerken.</p>\n\n<p>Met deze thesis willen we verder gaan kijken dan het traditionele netwerk aspect en bestuderen hoe in een bestaand draadloos netwerk services zoals DHCP, DNS, HTTP redundant kunnen worden gemaakt zodat het wegvallen van een van de nodes, niet tot gevolg kan hebben dat heel het netwerk faalt (single point-of-failure).</p>\n\n<p>Voor dit soort problemen kun je kijken naar oplossingen waarbij de protocols worden aangepast, of naar oplossingen die de services gaan dupliceren op meerdere nodes.  Het doel van de thesis is om in een eerste fase zich via een literatuur-studie te verdiepen in deze materie, en in een tweede fase te werken rond een demo die een van de oplossingen concreet uitwerkt in ons labo.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Uitbreiden van JabRef  (open source Java programma)','<p>JabRef is een open source programma om bibliografische gegevens te beheren. Niettegenstaande het reeds over veel functionaliteit beschikt, ontbreken er nog enkele praktische eigenschappen, zoals ook te zien op de \"Feature request page\". We denken hierbij onder meer aan: * integratie met AMS MathSciNet en Zentrallblatt * uniforme manier om bv. tijdschriften in voeren * uitbreiden van de zoekfunctionaliteit * verfijnen van het zoeken op duplicaten * ...</p>\r\n<p>Meer info over JabRef is te vinden op: http://jabref.sourceforge.net/</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Uplink pakket scheduling in LTE','<p>In LTE (Long Term Evolution), een nieuwe radio-access technologie voor mobiel breedband, moeten de tijd/frequentie resources voor data transmissie gedeeld worden door de verschillende gebruikers horend bij eenzelfde basisstation. De taak van het uplink scheduling algoritme is het verdelen van de beschikbare resources voor uplink data transmissie onder de verschillende gebruikers. Typisch houdt het scheduling algoritme rekening met de over tijd en frequentie varirende radio link condities van de verschillende gebruikers. </p>\n\n<p>De bedoeling van deze thesis is om uplink pakket scheduling in LTE te bestuderen. Hierbij zal eerst en vooral moeten uitgezocht worden hoe uplink data transmissie exact gebeurt in LTE en welke voorzieningen ter ondersteuning van het scheduling algoritme voorzien zijn in de LTE standaarden (bv. hoe verkrijgt het scheduling algoritme informatie over de link condities van de verschillende gebruikers, hoe wordt aan de gebruikers gesignaliseerd welke resources aan welke gebruiker werden toegekend, etc.). Ook is het de bedoeling een overzicht te maken van uplink scheduling algoritmes voorgesteld in de literatuur. Verdere stappen in de studie kunnen verschillende richtingen uit, zoals bijvoorbeeld het vergelijken van de performantie van verschillende algoritmes adhv een simulatie, het selecteren van een van de algoritmes uit de literatuur en bestuderen hoe het self-optimiserend kan gemaakt worden, ...</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Wireshark generic dissector: cross platform','<p>http://wsgd.free.fr/ cross platform\nzie ook http://wiki.wireshark.org/Development/Wishlist#head-48c01fb27b9bc3a5763a988e2ee349689b0fb65f\ntest it\nadd features</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Testen van FPU van een GPU','<p>De NVIDIA GTX 200 familie ondersteunt zowel single als double precision floating-point operaties.  In dit eindwerk willen we nagaan hoe goed de IEEE 754 ondersteuning is van deze GPU\'s, door gebruik te maken van de IeeeCC754 test tool.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Radio Simulation in Solarium','<p>The PATS research group uses the Sun SPOT technology as a basis for their sensornetwork related research. Although the hardware is nice to play with, the need for an efficient simulator is growing.</p>\n\n<p>Sun provides Solarium as a free platform in which virtual Sun SPOTs can be deployed and connected. The high-level abstraction is quite impressive (you can deploy any \'normal\' Sun SPOT application to a virtual Sun SPOT), but low level modelling of network related simulation code needs some large improvements.</p>\n\n<p>The goal of this thesis is to \n1. extend the model of the virtual Sun SPOT with a simulated radio chip on which the default network stack can be used without any modification\n2. improve the network related simulation code in order to make it possible to introduce more complex scenario\'s: which SPOTs can hear each other (unidirectional configuration should be possible), how can we introduce network quality fluctuations etc.</p>\n\n<p>Both the PATS research group and SUN are eager to get these improvements in Solarium. High-quality code will therefore be submitted to SUN to get it in one of the upcomming Solarium releases.</p>\n\n<p>More information can be found on \n* <a href=\"https://www.sunspotworld.com/\" title=\"Project Sun SPOT\">Sun SPOT World</a>\n* <a href=\"https://spots.dev.java.net/,\" title=\"SPOTs project\">SPOTs project on dev.java.net</a>\n* <a href=\"https://solarium.dev.java.net/\" title=\"Solarium Home\">Solarium</a>\n* [TOSSIM](http://www.cs.berkeley.edu/~pal/research/tossim.html, \"TinyOS simulator)</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Implementing an MDSOC virtual machine in Maxine','<p>Multi-dimensional separation of concerns (MDSOC) is an umbrella paradigm referring to several approaches which attempt to improve modularization. Examples include aspect-oriented and context-oriented programming.</p>\n\n<p>A virtual machine prototype dedicated to multi-dimensional separation of concerns has been developed in:</p>\n\n<p>[1] H. Schippers, M. Haupt, and R. Hirschfeld, An implementation substrate for languages composing modularized crosscutting concerns, Proceedings of the 2009 ACM symposium on Applied Computing,  Honolulu, Hawaii: ACM, 2009, pp. 1944-1951.</p>\n\n<p>The implementation framework was COLA (http://piumarta.net/software/cola). However, this framework is rather premature and in constant development.</p>\n\n<p>Hence, we would like to see a parallel implementation in Maxine, Sun\'s newest development (https://maxine.dev.java.net/).</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'an MDSOC Virtual Machine as execution engine for AToM3','<p>Multi-dimensional separation of concerns (MDSOC) is an umbrella paradigm referring to several approaches which attempt to improve modularization. Examples include aspect-oriented and context-oriented programming.</p>\n\n<p>A virtual machine prototype dedicated to multi-dimensional separation of concerns has been developed in:</p>\n\n<p>[1] H. Schippers, M. Haupt, and R. Hirschfeld, An implementation substrate for languages composing modularized crosscutting concerns, Proceedings of the 2009 ACM symposium on Applied Computing,  Honolulu, Hawaii: ACM, 2009, pp. 1944-1951.</p>\n\n<p>AToM3 (http://atom3.cs.mcgill.ca/) is a tool for multi-paradigm modeling, which has an execution engine.</p>\n\n<p>We would like to find out whether our virtual machine model can be used as execution engine of AToM3.</p>\n\n<p>This thesis consists of plugging our VM into AToM3\'s architecture and finding out whether or not it is sufficiently expressive to serve as AToM3\'s backend.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Scheduling Algorithm for Embedded Systems','<p>In order to run complex applications on multi-processor embedded systems, we represent them as Kahn Process Networks (KPN), a graph-based model. As the run-time overhead of the scheduler should be kept low, we compute schedules for subgraphs of KPNs at design-time. \nIn this thesis, the student should implement a scheduling technique that considers a multi-processor platform with heterogeneous processors and a Network-on-Chip. This scheduling algorithm should not only minimize execution times, but also take the costs for data transfers into account. Th student can start from an existing algorithm, implement and refine it. Programming language is C.</p>\n\n<p>[1] Gilles KAHN: The semantics of a simple language for parallel programming http://www1.cs.columbia.edu/~sedwards/papers/kahn1974semantics.pdf</p>\n\n<p>[2] Gilbert Ch. SIH: Multiprocessor scheduling to account for interprocessor communication http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Pubs/TechRpts/1991/1729.html</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Energy-efficient Schedules for Embedded Systems','<p>In order to run complex applications on multi-processor embedded systems, we represent them as Kahn Process Networks (KPN), a graph-based model. As the run-time overhead of the scheduler should be kept low, we compute schedules for subgraphs of KPNs at design-time.</p>\n\n<p>Embedded systems are often battery-powered and therefore the energy consumption of applications should be kept low. In this thesis, the student should implement and compare techniques to compute energy-efficient schedules. Programming language is C.</p>\n\n<p>[1] Gilles KAHN: The semantics of a simple language for parallel programming http://www1.cs.columbia.edu/~sedwards/papers/kahn1974semantics.pdf</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Mining Execution Traces','<p>Verschillende data mining methoden blijken zeer nuttig te zijn voor software engineers om het software engineering proces te optimaliseren.    In deze thesis is het de bedoeling om na te gaan in hoeverre patronen in execution traces inzicht kunnen geven over bepaalde software.  Er moet worden nagegaan in hoeverre bestaande pattern mining technieken zoals set mining en sequence mining technieken moeten aangepast worden om zo interessant mogelijke en meest bruikbare informatie te detecteren.  Deze aanpassingen moeten dan gemplementeerd en experimenteel gevalueerd worden.  Deze thesis sluit aan bij huidig onderzoek van de onderzoeksgroepen ADReM en LORE. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Biological Graph Mining','<p>Dankzij steeds snellere high throughput biotechnologische analysetechnieken kan men tegenwoordig het gedrag van duizenden componenten van een levende cel simultaan analyseren. In de bioinformatica heeft dit ertoe geleid dat men op basis van deze data een levend systeem kan modelleren als een netwerk (graph) van moleculaire componenten. Zulke netwerkmodellen werden intussen gegenereerd voor tal van organismen en op tal van niveau&rsquo;s. Voor de interpretatie van deze modellen is er echter nood aan data mining technieken op maat.</p>\r\n<p>In deze thesis zullen we vertrekken van eerder (binnen en buiten de Universiteit) ontwikkelde moleculaire interactie netwerkmodellen. Via verschillende data mining technieken zal daarin op zoek gegaan worden naar: - eigenschappen van knooppunten die frequent in elkaars buurt voorkomen - vaak wederkerende netwerkmotieven - clusters van sterk intergeconnecteerde componenten</p>\r\n<p>Het doel van deze thesis bestaat uit het ontwikkelen van algoritmen, het implementeren ervan en het toepassen ervan op een aantal re&euml;le netwerkmodellen.</p>\r\n<p>Voor deze thesis zal samengewerkt worden met bioinformatici die zullen helpen met de biologische interpretatie van de opgespoorde patronen.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Ontwerp en implementatie GPU gebaseerde algoritmen voor tomografie','<p>Tomografie is een techniek waarbij een drie-dimensionaal (3D) beeld van een object gemaakt wordt aan de hand van een serie projectiebeelden. Het meest bekende voorbeeld hiervan vinden we in de medische CT-scanner, die een 3D beeld maakt van een pati&euml;nt op basis van X-stralen beelden. De onderzoeksgroep ASTRA, die deel uitmaakt van <a href=\"http://visielab.uantwerpen.be/\">iMinds-Visielab</a>, richt zich op de ontwikkeling van nieuwe modellen, algoritmen en technologie&euml;n voor tomografie. De reeds ontwikkelde algoritmen zijn zeer krachtig, maar vragen bij het werken met grote datasets enorm veel rekenkracht. Als oplossing voor dit probleem zijn binnen ASTRA zowel software als hardwareconfiguraties ontwikkeld (ASTRA toolbox: <a href=\"http://www.astra-toolbox.com\">www.astra-toolbox.com</a>)&nbsp;die het mogelijk maken de rekenkracht van GPU&rsquo;s te benutten voor tomografie. Hierbij wordt gebruik gemaakt van het NVIDIA CUDA platform voor GPU computing.</p>\r\n<p>Op dit moment wordt binnen ASTRA gewerkt aan een softwarebibliotheek, waarmee een grote verscheidenheid aan 2D en 3D datasets kan worden verwerkt. GPU computing maakt hier een essentieel deel van uit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Het doel van deze thesis is het ontwerpen en implementeren van een uitbreiding van de huidige softwarebibliotheek die het mogelijk maakt de reconstructies gedistribueerd uit te voeren. Dit project zal bestaan uit twee fasen: - Het uitbreiden van de huidige single-threaded code naar een multi-core en multi-GPU model binnen een enkele workstation. Centraal hierbij staan het vermijden van conflicten tussen de threads en effectieve load-balancing. - Het ontwerpen en implementeren van een raamwerk voor distributed computing, waarbij meerdere instanties van de bibliotheek, op meedere werkstations, gelijktijdig aan een reconstructie werken.</p>\r\n<p>Gebruikte technologie&euml;n: - C++ - CUDA (voor GPU computing) - MPI (voor distributed computing)</p>\r\n<p>Werkomgeving:<a href=\"http://visielab.uantwerpen.be/\"> iMinds-Visielab</a> heeft inmiddels een reputatie opgebouwd op het gebied van GPU computing. Er is een grote verscheidenheid aan hardware beschikbaar waaronder krachtige workstations en gespecialiseerde NVIDIA TESLA hardware.</p>\r\n<p>Geinteresseerd? Kom er gerust eens over praten!</p>\r\n<p>Contact: jan.sijbers@uantwerpen.be</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Nano-FASTRA: desktop supercomputing voor elektronentomografie','<p>Tomografie is een techniek waarbij een drie-dimensionaal (3D) beeld van een object gemaakt wordt aan de hand van een serie projectiebeelden. Het meest bekende voorbeeld hiervan vinden we in de medische CT-scanner, die een 3D beeld maakt van een pati&euml;nt op basis van X-stralen beelden. Deze techniek wordt ook gebruikt voor het reconstrueren van nano-materialen, waarbij de projectiebeelden worden opgenomen met een elektronenmicroscoop. Voor elektronentomografie zijn diverse softwarepaketten beschikbaar, waaronder Tom-Toolbox, dat volledig in Matlab is ge&iuml;mplementeerd. Een nadeel van dit pakket is dat slechts zeer beperkte reconstructiealgoritmes worden ondersteund.</p>\r\n<p>Binnen de onderzoeksgroep ASTRA, die deel uitmaakt van <a href=\"http://visielab.uantwerpen.be/\">iMinds-Visielab</a>, wordt gewerkt aan de ontwikkeling van nieuwe modellen, algoritmen en technologie&euml;n voor tomografie, waarbij elektronentomografie een belangrijk toepassingsgebied vormt. De ontwikkelde software is ondergebracht in een objectgeori&euml;nteerde bibliotheek, op basis van C++ (kern) en Matlab (interface). Een belangrijke component hiervan vormt de GPU computing code, op basis van NVIDIA CUDA.</p>\r\n<p>Het doel van deze thesis is het analyseren, ontwerpen en implementeren van een gecombineerde toolbox voor elektronentomografie, op basis van de ASTRA-bibliotheek &nbsp;(<a href=\"http://www.astra-toolbox.com\">astra-toolbox.com</a>). Hiermee wordt het mogelijk de kracht van GPU&rsquo;s te gebruiken voor elektronentomografie. Bovendien kan een grote verscheidenheid aan algoritmes uit de ASTRA-bibliotheek worden gebruikt voor de reconstructie. Bij de integratie staan de volgende deeltaken centraal: - In kaart brengen van de workflow voor elektronentomografie, en het niveau waarop de ASTRA-code kan worden ge&iuml;ntegreerd. - Ontwerpen van interfaces voor de integratie tussen beide paketten en implementeren van conversie-routines voor uitwisseling van interne dataformaten - Snelheids en kwaliteitsvergelijking tussen de ASTRA-algoritmes (zowel CPU als GPU) en de oorspronkelijke Tom-Toolbox algoritmes.</p>\r\n<p>Gebruikte technologi&euml;n: - Matlab - C++ - CUDA (slechts om code te kunnen doorlezen)</p>\r\n<p>Werkomgeving: Het Visielab werkt op het gebied van elektronentomografie nauw samen met EMAT, het internationaal toonaangevend instituut voor elektronenmicroscopie in de materiaalkunde van de UA. Daarnaast heeft <a href=\"http://visielab.uantwerpen.be/\">iMinds-Visielab</a> inmiddels een reputatie opgebouwd op het gebied van GPU computing en behoort tot het NVIDIA Professor Partnership Program. Er is een grote verscheidenheid aan hardware beschikbaar: &nbsp;krachtige workstations en gespecialiseerde NVIDIA TESLA hardware.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Semantische kennis uit Wikipedia','<p>Een belangrijk struikelblok bij het bereiken van natuurlijke taalverwerking op menselijk niveau is het ontbreken van semantiek in de vorm van wereldkennis en domeinkennis (concepten en relaties tussen concepten: ontologien). Er zijn op dit moment twee methodes in gebruik om die kennis te verwerven: met de hand programmeren en automatisch extraheren op basis van grote hoeveelheden tekst. De eerste methode is tijdrovend en duur en kan alleen voor microdomeinen, de tweede methode leidt tot oppervlakkige kennis en beperkte bruikbaarheid.</p>\n\n<p>Wikipedia bestaat uit een reusachtige hoeveelheid tekst die gedeeltelijk gestructureerd is (definities en samenvattingen vooraan in elk artikel, infoboxes met de belangrijkste informatie, desambigueringspagina\'s en desambiguering in de tekst, verwijzingspagina\'s, ...). Recent is heel wat onderzoek opgestart rond het gebruik van Wikipedia voor de extractie van betekenis.</p>\n\n<p>Dit eindwerk zal in overleg met de student gestuurd worden tot een experiment naar de bruikbaarheid van uit Wikipedia afgeleide semantische kennis in de context van natuurlijke taalverwerkingsonderzoek bij CNTS en ADReM.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Visual Pattern Mining','<p>Verschillende pattern mining technieken leveren zeer grote hoeveelheden patronen op, waaronder talloze zeer gelijkaardige.  Een mogelijke oplossing hiervoor bestaat er uit al deze patronen te visualiseren onder het motto:\"a picture is worth a thousand words\".  Het doel van deze thesis is om verschillende visualisatie methoden te implementeren en hun toepasbaarheid te bestuderen op de pattern mining technieken die ontwikkeld werden binnen de ADReM onderzoeksgroep.  </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Eindwerken Agfa Graphics','<p>Elk jaar kunnen enkele studenten een eindwerk maken bij Agfa Graphics (divisie binnen Agfa-Gevaert die producten ontwikkelt voor de drukkerswereld). Er zijn i.h.b. mogelijkheden binnen de Prepress Portal groep die zich bezighoudt met de ontwikkeling van enterprise software systemen en web applicaties om de workflow van drukkerijen en de communicatie met hun klanten te optimaliseren (contactpersoon: Chris Tuijn).</p>\r\n<p>Technologieen/tools die gebruikt worden zijn o.a. Java, J2EE Application Servers, Eclipse, Hibernate en Flex (Adobe).</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Qt for VST','<p>VST (Virtual Studio Technology) is a software framework for developing real-time audio plug-ins, like synthesizers and audio effects. Every professional recording studio has, next to the necessary microphones and mixing panels, also a computer running software which is capable of loading VST plug-ins (Cubase, Max/MSP, ...). The technology is multiplatform for Windows and Mac.</p>\n\n<p>There exists a small open source GUI toolkit that has been made especially for VST plugins - see http://sourceforge.net/projects/vstgui/ . It is fast, lightweight and multiplatform, but unfortunately quite tedious to use, poorly documented, and very limited in functionality. Nevertheless, VSTGUI is often used as GUI framework for VST plugins since it is meant to be used for that purpose, and allows for extreme freedom in GUI design (read: you need to build every GUI more or less from scratch...).</p>\n\n<p>VST does not impose VSTGUI as GUI framework, in fact, VST allows you to use any GUI framework that you want. Using a few workarounds and the QMacNativeWidget class in combination with Boost threads, we\'ve already been able to come up with a way to control a VST plugin from a Qt GUI on Mac. This promises a whole lot of new GUI functionality, easily available for plugin developers. Therefore we think it\'s very useful to develop this further into a library of classes that bridge VST and Qt.</p>\n\n<p>This project has four distinct stages:\n1. Develop a set of cross-platform (windows/mac) software classes that bridges the Qt signal-slot system and VST\'s parameterized control system.\n2. Demonstrate that it works by replacing the GUI of two (or more) of the open-source MDA-VST project plugins ( http://sourceforge.net/projects/mda-vst/ ) with a Qt GUI of your own making.\n3. Benchmark the performance. This is one of the most important parts, since performance is of utmost importance in multimedia processing (every cycle counts). One of the reasons that people stick with lightweight toolkits like VSTGUI is that they fear that Qt is bloated and slow. We need to know if that is reality or myth.\n4. Write your findings on all of the above down into a bachelor\'s thesis.</p>\n\n<p>We are looking for a bachelor student with an interest in learning about Qt and real-time signal processing. Prior knowledge is not necessary. You do not need to know anything about music or audio, but an interest in digital audio effects is always handy when working on something like this. The programming language is C++. You need access to a Windows development environment - mac is optional. The project can be tailored to your skills and we welcome input and ideas of your own.</p>\n\n<p>This project is under supervision of Joachim Ganseman, Wim D\'haes and prof. Paul Scheunders of the VisionLab, at the department of Physics at the university of Antwerp. If you have interest in this project, please contact Joachim Ganseman. </p>\n\n<p>We are always interested in other project proposals involving the link between music and technology - if you have an project proposal of you own, come talk to us. Or if you know students in related disciplines (math/physics/engineering) at this or another university that could be interested in this kind of topic, feel free to inform them about us.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Bewegingscorrectie bij computer tomografie','<p>Tijdens CT beeldvorming wordt verondersteld dat het object of de patient stil blijft liggen. In de praktijk is dat zelden het geval, waardoor de ruimtelijke resolutie in het beeld sterk verminderd wordt. In deze thesis worden de oorzaken en gevolgen van beweging bestudeerd. Vervolgens worden nieuwe methoden onderzocht om dit probleem aan te pakken.Hierbij wordt gebruik gemaakt van de reconstructiebibliotheek die werd ontwikkeld voor de Fastra (fastra.ua.ac.be).</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Domain-Specific Modelling and Model Transformation  for Google Android applications','<p>Android is a software stack for mobile devices that includes an operating system, middleware and key applications. The Android SDK provides the tools and APIs to develop applications that run on Android-powered devices such as the HTC Magic smartphone.</p>\n\n<p>Domain-Specific Modelling (DSM) and Model Transformation (MT) have the potential to support rapid development and synthesis of new applications on Android.</p>\n\n<p>This thesis investigates the power and limitations of DSM and MT. As an example challenge, the automatic synthesis of Android applications is only industrially relevant if debugging and testing is supported. The thesis will build some demonstrator applications and generalize from them.</p>\n\n<p>This will be based on <a href=\"http://msdl.cs.mcgill.ca/presentations/08.08.29.MSDLsummer/presentations/RaphaelMannadiar.presentation.pdf\">preliminary work</a>\n by <a href=\"http://msdl.cs.mcgill.ca/people/raphael/\">Raphael Mannadiar</a>.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Modelling and Transformation for Non-Player Characters in massively multiplayer games','<p>Recently, the complexity of modern, real-time computer games has increased drastically. The need for sophisticated game AI, in particular for Non-Player Characters (NPCs), grows with the demand for realistic games. Writing consistent, re-useable and efficient AI code has become hard. Modelling game AI at an appropriate abstraction level using an appropriate modelling language based on Statecharts has many advantages. </p>\n\n<p>This thesis will explore the modelling, simulation and automatic synthesis of NPC behaviour. This work will elaborate on the MoDELS paper <a href=\"http://www.springerlink.com/content/u7uw376414233471/\">Model-Based Design of Computer-Controlled Game Character Behavior </a>. The <a href=\"http://www.gamasutra.com/php-bin/news_index.php?story=7056:\">TankWars game</a> will be used as a starting point. The <a href=\"http://mammoth.cs.mcgill.ca/\">Mammoth multiplayer game research framework</a> will be used as a target platform.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Mijn docop: doctoraatsopleiding gedigitaliseerd','<p>Aan de Universiteit Antwerpen moeten alle doctorandi een doctoraatsopleiding volgen. Op <a href=\"http://www.ua.ac.be/main.aspx?c=*DOCOP&amp;n=34159\">http://www.ua.ac.be/main.aspx?c=*DOCOP&amp;n=34159</a> staan dan ook een veel activiteiten die gekozen kunnen worden. Elk van die activiteiten kan punten opleveren voor het voltooien van de doctoraatsopleiding.</p>\r\n<p>Echter, heel veel gebeurt nog manueel. De cursussen moeten manueel online gezet worden, een inschrijving moet manueel verwerkt worden en doctorandi kunnen zelf ook nergens zien welke activiteiten ze al gevolgd hebben. Laat staan dat zichtbaar is hoeveel punten nog gehaald moeten worden en of alles goedgekeurd is.</p>\r\n<p>De bedoeling van dit eindwerk is dan ook het ontwikkelen van een systeem om dat alles te vereenvoudigen. De doctoraatsstudent zal kunnen inloggen op een eigen doctoraatsopleiding portfolio en zien welke cursussen hoeveel punten kregen, welke inschrijvingen goedgekeurd zijn, enzovoort. De coordinator van de doctoraatsopleiding zal alles kunnen coordineren en bijvoorbeeld inschrijvingen goedkeuren en activiteiten goedkeuren.</p>\r\n<p>Om in de toekomst goed onderhoudbaar te zijn en geen dubbel werk te doen, stellen we voor om te vertrekken van Drupal. Dit CMS is zeer krachtig en kan al veel, zodat geconcentreerd kan worden op de specifieke problemen.</p>\r\n<p>We verwachten dat alle aanpassingen en patches aan Drupal gedocumenteerd worden en gedeeld worden met Drupal, zodat in de toekomst van een standaard, niet-gepatchte versie vertrokken kan worden. Om de installatie zelf te versnellen wordt verwacht dat een zogenaamd install profile gemaakt wordt. Verder is gebruiksvriendelijkheid zeer belangrijk, omdat dit systeem ook moet gebruikt worden door niet-informatici. Daarom moet een goede studie gemaakt worden van gebruikersbehoeften, bv. met mockups. Regelmatig overleg en rapportering met de gebruikers is cruciaal.</p>\r\n<p>Specifieke gebruikte technologieen: - de Drupal API - PHP in het algemeen - LDAP voor authenticatie tegen de UA servers - HTML en CSS voor layout (beperkt, we hebben Drupal UA themes)</p>\r\n<p>Vereisten: - zin om Drupal goed te leren kennen - gebruiksvriendelijkheid hoog inschatten - in staat zijn tot grondige documentatie van design en implementatie</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Robot Monitoring and Control Library','<p>Within the PATS group we have been designing an approach, called reflective-and-refractive variables (RR vars), which allows adaptive-and-dependable systems to be expressed and managed in a straightforward and intuitive way.</p>\r\n<p>From the point of view of the programmer, RR vars are just variables with a predefined name and type; for instance &ldquo;<tt>cpu</tt>&rdquo;, &ldquo;<tt>mplayer</tt>&rdquo;, &ldquo;<tt>bandwidth</tt>&rdquo;, and &ldquo;<tt>watchdog</tt>&rdquo;. As it is the case for \"normal\" variables, RR vars are associated with some memory cells; the key difference is twofold:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>First of all, in the case of RR vars, those memory cells have &ldquo;volatile&rdquo; contents: their value can change unexpectedly, and provide for instance an estimation of the current amount of CPU being used on some processing node; or the current state of a media player; or an estimation of the end-to-end bandwidth between two processing nodes; or the current state of a task being guarded by a watchdog timer. We use to say that each variable <em>reflects</em> the value of a certain property.</li>\r\n<li>Furthermore, changing one of these variables can trigger an adjustment of some parameter, e.g., resetting a watchdog timer or changing the frame dropping policy of a video player. If that is the case, we use to say that writes <em>refract</em> and trigger a request for adaptation of their corresponding properties.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Objective</strong><br /> The aim of this project work is to extend the set of RR vars and to apply this concept to monitor and control a Lego Mindstorms NXT robot so as to perform simple tasks by inspecting and writing a set of RR vars.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://cache.lego.com/upload/contentTemplating/MindstormsOverview/images/2057/picA44E6DB5-BD00-4555-978B-F14B2F3977B7.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>The student shall first learn how to create new RR vars, then how to access the value of the sensors of the robot, and how to control the robot so as to do simple tasks. Then (s)he will design new RR var returning the sensor values and performing those control actions. A simple demo shall be set up to demonstrate the new way to perform simple robotic tasks.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Object Representations in Computer Aided Design');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Designing experiments for the optimization of nano-material manufacturing','<p>Buckypaper (BP) is a thin sheet made from an aggregate of carbon nanotubes that are approximately 50,000 times thinner than a human hair. This promising new material has potential applications ranging from building aerospace vehicles to the next generation electronics and displays.</p>\n\n<p>Associated Press (17/10/2008): Future Planes, Cars May Be Made of Buckypaper<br />\nYoutube: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hkijxr4z_mY<br />\nBuckypaper (Wikipedia): http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Buckypaper</p>\n\n<p>The quality of BP is determined by various factors in the manufacturing process. To determine the factors that can deliver the optimized production, the traditional engineering approach relies on the domain knowledge and the control of one-factor-at-a-time. This may not be feasible since the properties of a new material are usually not completely clear and experiments can be expensive. It has been shown that the design of experiment can be an effective approach to meet the above challenges.</p>\n\n<p>Currently, the design of experiment approach is mainly built upon statistical methods. This project investigates the possibility of taking further advantage of recent results of numerical black-box algorithms in the design of experiment.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'The role of structure in service reliability','<p>The phenomenon of Skype and other Voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP) services has attracted a great deal of attention and research. As the user base is growing every day, providing reliable and satisfactory voice services has become a high priority. This is nevertheless a subtle issue: while users prefer calls with high quality voice that requires a higher bit rate, sending voice data with unnecessary high bit rates over a network is likely to cause congestion and undermine the overall quality. Lately, research is devoted to the study of adapting data rate to network conditions [1].</p>\r\n<p>To evaluate the reliability condition of a complicated network is a difficult job. Simulations based on random sampling have already been used [2]. Recently, researchers are making progress by employing some statistical methods.</p>\r\n<p>Since a complicated network is composed from basic configurations of series and parallel, it is worth to attempt methods that can take into consideration the building structure of the network system. This is the research topic of the project. If possible, we plan to investigate the possibility of integrating our techniques in the evaluation of services such as Skype that are provided over network and sensitive to its condition.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Huang, T.-Y., Chen, K.-T., and Huang, P. Tuning Skype\'s Redundancy Control Algorithm for User Satisfaction. In Proceedings of the 28th Conference on Computer Communications (INFOCOM 2009), Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, April 2009.</li>\r\n<li>Yeh, W.-C. A MCS-RSM Approach for Network Reliability to Minimise the Total Cost. Int. J. Adv. Manuf Technol 22: 681-688 (2003).</li>\r\n</ol>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Modeling a Network of Energy Transmission and Distribution');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Mathematics for Smart Power ','<p>While many think the future of green energy as solar plants or wind turbines, one of the most potent options is actually efficiency. The heavily promoted smart grid, a digital system that can adapt various conditions in the routing of electricity, is viewed as one of the solutions to save energy and reduce cost.</p>\n\n<p>Example: A Smart Grid for Intelligent Energy Use (IEEE Tech Activities)<br />\nYoutube: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YrcqA_cqRD8<br />\nDoing the Math for Smart Power (Clemson World: Spring 2009)<br />\nhttp://www.clemson.edu/clemsonworld/2009/spring/article3.html</p>\n\n<p>The control and design of such a network system inevitably encounter a model that is often highly complicated. Besides to evaluate the system behavior, it is usually desirable to optimize the cost and resource. Using random sampling, Monte Carlo simulation has been implemented to evaluate complicated network systems. Recently, statistical methods have shown promise to provide another effective tool to this problem. The highly complicated nature of the problem poses challenges to mathematicians, statisticians, as well as computer scientists and engineers.</p>\n\n<p>Comparing to the overall system performance, the infrastructure (or the hardware) of a network system is manageable and can usually be obtained. Moreover, such a system is composed from a finite number of configurations, e.g. series, parallel, etc. So far, neither the probabilistic nor the statistical approach seems to fully utilize such information. This project targets this additional possibility. We have developed a series of numerical black-box algorithms that can reveal the algebraic structure of a model. This project investigates the possibility of taking advantage of these algorithms in the evaluation and control of such a network model.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Eclipse Plugin for Click Modular Router Development','<p>Het CLICK Modular Router platform vormt een krachtige en flexibele omgeving voor het ontwikkelen van routers. Click is gebaseerd op het concept dat een router kan worden opgebouwd uit een aantal elementen die verantwoordelijk zijn voor het verwerken van pakketten en het opslaan van informatie. Deze elementen worden met elkaar verbonden in een graaf (beschreven in een script) die de opeenvolgende stappen van het verwerken van het pakket beschrijft op een gestructureerde manier. Deze aanpak verhoogt de modulariteit van de geimplementeerde protocols, alsook de mogelijkheid om elementen te hergebruiken. Standaard bied CLICK een reeks van elementen aan om IPv4, IPv6, Ethernet en 802.11 pakketten te verwerken alsook verschilende elementen die scheduling en queueing algoritmes implementeren.</p>\n\n<p>De bedoeling van dit project is om de basis te leggen voor een Eclipse Plugin die toelaat Click scripts en Elementen op een eenvoudige wijze te ontwikkelen.</p>\n\n<p>Om dit te doen dient er vooral gewerkt te worden aan een goede UI voor het grafisch editeren van een click graph. Het is hier de bedoeling dat de student op basis van de input van de begeleider(s) een UI concept uit te werken en dit samen te verfijnen.</p>\n\n<p>Aangezien CLICK elementen in C++ worden geschreven dient deze plugin ook op een goede manier samen te werken met de CDT plugin die reeds beschikbaar is voor Eclipse. Het zou hier dan vooral gaan om het correct genereren van templates.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Deploying and XMPP architecture for server monitoring and management','<p>Uit Jabber dat vooral gericht was om IM diensten te implementeren is het Extensible Messaging and Presence Protocol gegroeid dat zich uitbreid naar bericht-georinteerde middleware. Door de grote beschikbaarheid van XMPP gerelateerde software (libraries), de generische architectuur, de mogelijkheid om firewalls via HTTP te omzeilen is XMPP uitgegroeid tot meer dan een IM service. </p>\n\n<p>Binnen PATS zien we met de mogelijkheid om XMPP als een transport en authenticatie middel te gebruiken om onze netwerk toestellen op een veilige manier te beheren.</p>\n\n<p>De bedoeling van deze stage is uit te zoeken hoe XMPP kan gebruikt worden om netwerk toestellen toe monitoren (status, uptime, statistics) en te beheren (update, configuratie, reboot, etc.). Dit doe je door in samenwerking met de begeleider op zoek te gaan naar software (XMPP server, XMPP client library) die past bij de bestaande infrastructuur bij PATS en een test opstelling uitbouwt.  </p>\n\n<p>We verwachten van de student in kwestie een gedetailleerd verslag te maken van zijn activiteit zodat dit werk later kan worden nagemaakt.</p>\n\n<p>Een aantal interessante links</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://xmpp.org/\">http://xmpp.org/</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://socialvpn.wordpress.com/\">http://socialvpn.wordpress.com/</a></li>\n</ul>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'BRDF modeling for efficient photorealistic computer graphics','<h3>PHOTOREALISTIC COMPUTER GRAPHICS</h3>\r\n<p>The computing power of modern GPU\'s opens the door for stunningly photorealistc interactive 3D content. While the realization of realtime computer-generated images indistinguishable from photographs remains as yet unreached, one piece of machinery that will play an important role in realising interactive photorealism is the notion of a bidirectional reflectance distribution function (BRDF) [1] and BRDF-based lighting techniques [2,3].</p>\r\n<h3>WHAT ARE BRDF\'s?</h3>\r\n<p>A BRDF basically describes the appearance of a material by its interaction with light at a surface point: it describes how much light is reflected when light makes contact with the material.</p>\r\n<h3>BRDF MODELING</h3>\r\n<p>Several physically-based BRDF models (or theoretical models) have been proposed. Such models often make too restrictive assumptions or may become extremely complex when it is requiered that they agree well with actual measured BRDF data. With the increasing demand for flexibilty and high performance of such models, empirical modeling techniques [4] have gained the interest of the community. The rescent advances in requiering a lot of real BRDF data with a low noise level make such techniques even more attractive. It has been observed that rational functions [5] are particularly suited for capturing important BRDF characteristics. This project investigates the use of state of the art approximation techniques in BRDF modeling.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bidirectional_Reflectance_Distribution_Function</li>\r\n<li>An Introduction to BRDF-Based Lighting, Chrus Wynn, NVIDIA Corporation</li>\r\n<li>http://developer.nvidia.com/object/BRDFbased_Lighting.html</li>\r\n<li>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Empirical_modelling</li>\r\n<li>http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rational_function</li>\r\n</ol>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Priority in Multiple Access Systems using Combinatorial Designs','<p>Recently, combinatorial designs have been used to improve the throughput on random access channels without feedback (e.g., the contention channel in DVB-RCS satellite links). A traditional solution for channels without feedback exists in transmitting each packet R times in the next N slots by randomly selecting R out of these N slot, in the hope that at least one transmission is successful. Combinatorial designs on the other hand assign a user code to each user in the system. This length R code identifies the R slots that the user will use in case he has some data available. The class of 2-(N,R,1) designs is of particular interest as it guarantees that two users share at most one of the N slots. </p>\n\n<p>In this thesis we wish to enrich the above system such that the users can be classified in two groups: high priority users and low priority users. Such that high priority users are more likely to be successful than their low priority counterparts. One can think of several ways to support these priority classes and the main objective of this thesis is to investigate which solution is the most effective. Also, in order to assess the performance of a particular solution, explicit expressions for the success probabilities should be obtained whenever possible. Simulation studies are used as a means to confirm the analytical results.</p>\n\n<p>This thesis is mostly of a mathematical nature, where the programming component is rather limited.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'L-systems and Computer Graphics','<p>L-systems were traditionally developed to give a compact description of biological components, such as trees, plants, etc. They are also very useful to generate 2 and 3 dimensional fractal images. </p>\n\n<p>This thesis aims at implementing a software package to generate images that can be described using an L-system. It should support 2D and 3D L-systems (also known as turtle graphics), stochastic L-systems, L-systems with brackets, etc.</p>\n\n<p>Special attention will also be paid to the time and memory complexity of the implementation. Possible solutions caused by the lack of memory should also be investigated. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Algorithms for Flow Network Problems','<p>Flow network problems, as discussed in the course \"Data Structures and (Graph) Algorithms\", form a fundamental class of optimization problems for which many efficient algorithms have been developed (e.g., Ford-Fulkerson, Edmonds-Karp, Preflow-Push algorithms, etc.). The objective of this thesis is to implement a number of these algorithms and to perform a large scale experimental study to compare the time complexity of these algorithms and to check whether the asymptotic complexity (analyzed in the course notes) is also appropriate for small to medium size problems. Apart from the algorithms discussed in the course notes other solutions can be implemented as well (e.g., maximum capacity augmenting path).</p>\n\n<p>Optionally, the operation of these algorithms on small-scale problems can also be visualized. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Building Hybrid Clouds with Amazon EC2 and Google AppEngine','<p>Het outsourcen van IT infrastructuur en zijn beheer heeft recent een extra boost gekregen door de producten die \"cloud\" providers zoals Amazon en Google recent op de markt hebben gebracht. Hierbij wordt klanten de mogelijkheid geboden om via een betaling per gebruikte eenheid resource, en zonder voorafgaandelijke minimum investeringen, gebruik te maken van IT infrastructuur (rekenkracht, opslagruimte, ...), in hun datacenters. Zulk een gebruik is de laatste jaren mogelijk geworden zonder hoge overhead aan configuratie van systemen en applicatie door gebruik te maken van virtualizatie technologie (Xen, VMWare, Microsoft). </p>\n\n<p>Door de schaalvoordelen die cloud providers zoals Amazon en Google kunnen realizeren in de aankoop en beheer van hun infrastructuur, kunnen zij aan competitieve prijzen toegang tot IT infrastructuur aanbieden. Bovendien zorgt hun gebruiksmodel voor een mate van flexibiliteit die een intern data center onmogelijk kan bieden. </p>\n\n<p>Voor vele partijen is het outsourcing verhaal echter geen zwart/wit verhaal. Zo wil men ook de interne infrastructuur zo efficient mogelijk blijven gebruiken, en on-demand beroep doen op diensten van derde partijen wanneer een piek in de belasting van de infrastructuur daarom vraagt. Verder zijn er aspecten rond beveiliging en confidentialiteit van data waarmee rekening moet gehouden worden indien gebruik wordt gemaakt van (een) cloud provider(s). </p>\n\n<p>De actuele vraag bestaat dan ook om de interne infrastructuur op een transparante maar beveiligde wijze uit te breiden met infrastructuur van derde partijen, om zo een \"hybrid\" cloud te bekomen. De term hybrid verwijst naar de combinatie van een interne infrastructuur (private cloud) en een externe infrastructuur (public cloud). </p>\n\n<p>Hiervoor werden door Amazon en Google zeer recent extra diensten ontwikkeld. De doelstelling van deze stage is om deze diensten grondig onder te evalueren en te kijken in welke mate zij de problematiek die gepaard gaat met het opzetten van een hybride cloud aanpakken.  </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Limitations and opportunities for interactive applications on cloud resources ','<p>Cloud computing [3, 4, 5] is een model waarbij o.m. rekenkracht en applicaties via het internet (de cloud) toegankelijk zijn. Amazon biedt sinds 2006 via haar EC2-webservice [1] de mogelijkheid om on-the-fly rekenkracht in de vorm van virtuele machines te huren. Daarvoor heeft het de afgelopen jaren gigantische datacenters neergepoot.</p>\n\n<p>Tijdens deze stage zal je onderzoeken tot op welke hoogte interactieve applicaties op clouds kunnen gehost worden. De vereisten op vlak van de client apparatuur en de netwerk connectie van deze apparatuur met de cloud moet hiervoor in kaart worden gebracht. Verder zullen een aantal technieken bestudeerd worden om tot efficiente beeld compressie/decompressie te komen om interactieve applicaties mogelijk te maken op resource constrained devices. Recent is AMD met een het FusionRender initiatief gestart om dit idee uit te werken, en meerdere spelers betreden nu deze markt [1]. </p>\n\n<p>Het komt er dus op neer om tijdens deze stage de mogelijkheden en beperkingen van deze aanpak in kaart te brengen. In een daaropvolgende stage of eindwerk kunnen specifieke uitdagingen in dit kader uitgewerkt en geevalueerd worden. </p>\n\n<p>[1] http://blogs.amd.com/unprocessed/tag/fusion-render-cloud/</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Evaluating the performance of continuations ','<p>Computergebaseerde simulaties zijn een onmisbare tool geworden in veel takken van de wetenschap om nieuwe algoritmen, systemen en technieken te evalueren op een kost efficiente manier.</p>\r\n<p>Voor de simulatie van gedistribueerde systemen waarin meerdere gedistribueerde processen met elkaar communiceren over een netwerk, gebruikt de CoMP groep een discrete-event simulator. Deze simulator maakt gebruik van \"continuations\" als alternatief voor een klassieke massive multi-threaded approach in Java. Continuations hebben het voordeel dat de programmeur zelf volledige controle heeft op het schedulen van parallelle processen, iets wat in discrete-event simulaties goed van pas komt. Bovendien kan men met continuations grootschaligere simulaties tot uitvoering brengen in vergelijking met klassieke threads.</p>\r\n<p>Continuations worden aangeleverd door de Javaflow library van het Apache project. Kilim is een alternatieve library ontwikkeld aan de universiteit van Cambridge, die onder synthetische benchmarks een veel hogere performantie behaalt. Het gebruik van Aspect Oriented Programming in onze simulator conflicteert echter met het \"fiber\" (i.e. thread context) passing mechanisme dat door Kilim wordt gebruikt.</p>\r\n<p>Het doel van dit onderzoek is het uitwerken van een oplossing voor deze incompatibiliteit (hiervoor zijn reeds enkele ideeen voorhanden), en een grondige studie te maken van de performantiewinst die de Kilim library oplevert voor een aantal simulatie scenario\'s. Verder is het interessant om meer accuraat de performantiewinst van continuations te kwantificeren in vergelijking met een klassieke multi-threaded approach.</p>\r\n<p>[1] S. Srinivasan, A Thread of One\'s Own, New Horizons in Compilers Workshop, Bangalore. www.malhar.net/sriram/kilim/thread<em>of</em>ones_own.pdf</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Further development and deployment of a self-recovering SunSPOT testbed','<p>A basic self recovering, watchdog based SunSPOT testbed was developed in a thesis last year. Although the initial goals of this thesis were achieved, a lot of work can still be done to ameliorate the quality of the SunSPOT based testbed:\n- Thorough testing (and probably bug fixing) of the existing code\n- Initial deployment\n- Making the whole testbed more user-friendly\n- Improving the introduced concepts and some code\n- Integrating virtual SPOTs into the testbed setup\n- Integrating the testbed into TERRAN\n- ...</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Artificial Intelligence for Lego Mindstorms Robots','<p>De bedoeling van dit project is om technieken uit de artificiele intelligentie toe te passen op de Lego Mindstorms Robots. Dit door een specifieke (spel) omgeving te cre&euml;ren en de robot daarin te laten bewegen, \'redeneren\', en zijn opdracht te laten uitvoeren.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Querying music score databases','<p>Online music databases are nothing new: everyone knows iTunes and online radio services like last.fm. But when it comes down to music scores (sheet music), the possibilities are very limited. Even the largest online score databases, like www.imslp.org, are usually built from pdf images of (badly) scanned sheet music. The first small steps in the direction of MusicXML score databases (e.g. www.wikifonia.org ) offer only limited possibilities for the moment.</p>\n\n<p>If a native XML-database is used to store a large collection of music scores in the MusicXML format, one can retrieve music according to criteria that your average search engine could only dream of:\n- find all the score in which only a limited set of notes or chords occurs\n- find all scores with the word \"computer\" somewhere in the lyrics\n- find all occurrences of a certain melodic or rhythmic motive in the database\n- give me all songs in c minor by a certain artist\n- i need waltzes with a tempo lower than 80 bpm, no note faster than an 8th, and less than 2 pages long.\n- etc...</p>\n\n<p>Creating queries for these kind of questions is quite straightforward and does not take much effort. The MusicXML format is a widely accepted standard now, native XML databases with good XQuery engines exist. What we need now is to combine it all, see whether the performance is adequate, and if so, make it available for the public online.</p>\n\n<p>In this project, you set up a website that allows users to access a music score database and query it with the degree of control demonstrated above. The following set of functionality can be seen as the basic requirements - but we welcome any fresh and new ideas that might add to the functionality or usability of this kind of website:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>deploy a native XML database of choice (we mainly used eXist in our experiments). We will provide you with server space and an initial dataset.</li>\n<li>build a website that connects to this database, using a framework like OpenLaszlo, Ruby on Rails, ...</li>\n<li>use OpenID to provide a login system, so people can make manage their own collections of scores.</li>\n<li>build an advanced search interface that allows users to query the database using XQuery.</li>\n<li>get the results displayed adequately. We do NOT require you to write a system to display music scores - there is other software that can do that for you if necessary.</li>\n<li>try to provide mash-ups with other services: providing links to online radio stations next to the results, ...</li>\n<li>write down your findings in a bachelor\'s thesis.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>This project has been set up as a bachelor\'s thesis project. We are looking for a student with an interest in web applications, XML databases and XQuery. You need to be able to read music. Prior knowledge of XML databases and XQuery is not necessary but is handy. Also, the more experience in web development you have, the better. The extent of the assignment will be adapted to your capabilities. </p>\n\n<p>This project is under supervision of Joachim Ganseman, Wim D\'haes and prof. Paul Scheunders of the VisionLab, at the department of Physics at the university of Antwerp. If you have interest in this project, please contact Joachim Ganseman. </p>\n\n<p>We are always interested in other project proposals involving the link between music and technology - if you have an project proposal of you own, come talk to us. Or if you know of students in related disciplines (math/physics/engineering) at this or another university that could be interested in this kind of topic, feel free to inform them about us.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'DataDia - Poussenier bvba','<p>DataDia is een volledig software platform bedoeld om alle bedrijfsprocessen binnen 1 enkele omgeving te integreren. Het is ontwikkeld op basis van open source software (Linux - Apache - PostgreSQL - PHP) dit om dure operating costs en vendor lock-in te vermijden. De applicatie zelf draait op een in huis ontwikkeld event-driven PHP framework. Projecten:</p>\r\n<p>Voorraadsysteem:</p>\r\n<p>Voorraadposten: Er is momenteel een heel basic voorraadsysteem ge&iuml;mplementeerd, dit wil zeggen dat er per product een het aantal, gewicht e.d. wordt opgeslagen. Dit zouden we willen uitbreiden naar een systeem met verschillende voorraadposten. Waarbij ook de nodige gebruikersschermen ontwikkeld moeten worden voor het beheren van de voorraden.</p>\r\n<p>Import/Export: We willen onze toepassing beter laten aansluiten met bestaande applicaties. Opgeslagen contactpersonen binnen het systeem zouden bijvoorbeeld eenvoudig ge&iuml;mporteerd/ge&euml;xporteerd of gesyncroniseerd moeten kunnen worden van/naar MS Exchange, Google Apps, ...</p>\r\n<p>Prijzen en commissiesysteem:</p>\r\n<p>Prijsbeleid: Momenteel is er een heel eenvoudig systeem ge&iuml;mplementeerd met betrekking tot het prijsbeleid. Prijzen worden namelijk opgeslagen en aangepast per product. Dit zou verder moeten ontwikkeld worden tot een meer dynamisch systeem waarbij prijzen afhankelijk worden van niet enkel het product maar ook bijvoorbeeld de groep(en) waartoe dit product behoort, de klant van een offerte, mogelijke prijsacties, ...</p>\r\n<p>Commissieberekening: Samen met de uitbreiding op het prijsbeleid zou er ook een commissiesysteem ontwikkeld moeten worden waarbij resellers een commissie ontvangen op verkochte goederen. Dit in combinatie met een systeem van webcodes waarbij klanten op een centrale website hun ontvangen webcode (van de reseller) invoegen en automatisch de correcte commissies worden verrekend.</p>\r\n<p>Extra:</p>\r\n<p>In beide objecten hebben jullie de kans om in een kleine bedrijfsomgeving terecht te komen waar jullie werk rechtstreeks getoetst wordt aan de realiteit met onmiddelijke feedback. Een volledig productie -en distributieproces kan worden opgevolgd op een oppervlakte van nog geen 100m&sup2;. DataDia is momenteel al de achterliggende engine voor twee websites in de diamantsector en meerdere zijn in ontwikkeling.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Location based public transport planning on Android','<p>Het gebruik van de GSM in het dagelijkse leven is niet meer weg te denken. De functionaliteit van de toestellen breidt in deze dan ook steeds maar uit. Het gaat zelfs zo ver dat de hedendaagse nieuwe toestellen in vele gevallen zijn uitgerust met een GPS module. Zo ook de hedendaagse toestellen met het Android operating system. In deze bachelor thesis is het de bedoeling om een proof of concept implementatie te maken van een openbaar vervoer navigatie programma. Concreet is het de bedoeling dat het programma je volgens de vooraf opgelegde constraints (zo goedkoop mogelijk, zo snel mogelijk, ...) van punt A naar punt B brengt gebruik makend van het openbaar vervoer. Er dient hier dan rekening gehouden te worden met de nabijheid van haltes of stations, van de timetables van het openbaar vervoer en van de snelheid van de vervoersmiddelen.</p>\n\n<p>Concreet bestaat het project uit een aantal stappen. In de eerste stap moet nagegaan worden waar de informatie omtrent de timetables en de berekening van de route moet gebeuren. Er moet nagegaan worden of de beperkte dataopslag en de beperkte computationele middelen van een mobile device voldoende zijn om het navigatie programma te ondersteunen.  In een tweede stap moet er een shortest path algoritme uitgewerkt worden dat rekening houdend met de verschillende constraints en de timetables de beste route berekent tot het doel. Tot slot dient dit pad aan de hand van de huidige GPS-coordinaten van de gebruiker opgevolgd en waar nodig aangepast te worden. Zo dient een gebruiker verwittigd te worden wanneer hij van een bus of trein moet afstappen; hij dient te weten naar welke halte hij zich moet begeven en welk vervoersmiddel hij op welk tijdstip moet nemen, enz.</p>\n\n<p>Het doel van de thesis is dat er aan de hand van een eenvoudige doch doordachte implementatie wordt aangetoond dat het ontwikkelen van een openbaar vervoer navigatieplatform voor mobile devices al dan niet haalbaar is.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Forest growth prediction');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Web-based GUI builder','<p>Context</p>\n\n<p>Het beheren en onderhouden van grafische gebruikersinterfaces (GUI\'s) ligt veelal bij de softwareontwikkelaar en gebruikersinterface-specialist. Gewone gebruikers beschikken niet onmiddellijk over software die hen in staat stelt tot het ontwerpen van gebruikersinterfaces, terwijl ze dikwijls toch een concreet beeld hebben dat ze dan meteen zouden kunnen concretiseren en verder verfijnen.</p>\n\n<p>Doel</p>\n\n<p>Het doel van dit eindwerk omvat het ontwerpen van een webapplicatie die de gebruiker in staat stelt interactieve grafische user interfaces te bouwen en op te slaan.op een gebruiksvriendelijke manier. Het is ook mogelijk deze te exporteren naar XML-formaten die bruikbaar zijn voor concrete softwareprojecten. Het interne opslagformaat beschrijft de gebouwde grafische interfaces zo abstract mogelijk, zodat de applicatie gebruikt kan worden voor diverse platformen.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Suitablility evaluation of the Azure Cloud Framework for scientific applications','<p>Een van de hotste topics in hedendaagse IT wereld is Cloud computing, een model waarbij applicaties niet langer lokaal maar wel op servers draaien, en aangestuurd worden over het internet (de cloud). De twee bekendste voorbeelden hiervan zijn Google Apps en Amazon EC2. Terwijl Google diverse applicaties via de webbrowser ter beschikking stelt van gebruikers, laat Amazon toe om in enkele seconden een (bijna) ongelimiteerd aantal servers, in de vorm van virtuele machines, op te starten en te beheren. Bij cloud computing wordt meestal gebruik gemaakt van een pay-as-you-go model: je betaalt enkel voor de tijd die je applicatie of server gebruikt. </p>\n\n<p>Ook Microsoft doet een poging om voet aan wal te krijgen bij het hele Cloud Computing gebeuren. Azure Service Platform is een applicatieplatform dat toelaat applicaties te ontwikkelen die rechtstreeks in datacenters van Microsoft uitgerold kunnen worden. Daarmee opent het deuren voor wetenschappelijke applicaties. Zon wetenschappelijke applicaties zijn dikwijls erg computationeel en/of data-intensief. Resultaten kunnen met traditionele methoden vaak dagen of weken op zich laten wachten, en kunnen erg duur zijn. </p>\n\n<p>Doel van deze onderzoekstage is de evaluatie van de geschiktheid van het Azure-platform voor de bouw en uitrol van zon applicaties: betekent het gebruik van Azure voor computationele of data-intensieve applicaties een meerwaarde op vlak van kost, snelheid en gebruiksgemak ten opzichte van bijvoorbeeld een private rekencluster of Amazon EC2?</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Optimizing instance type selection and application scaling in IaaS clouds','<p>Een van de meest besproken topics in de hedendaagse IT wereld is &ldquo;Cloud computing&rdquo;, een model waarbij applicaties niet langer lokaal maar wel op servers draaien, en aangestuurd worden over het internet (de &ldquo;cloud&rdquo;). De twee bekendste voorbeelden hiervan zijn Google Apps en Amazon EC2. Terwijl Google diverse applicaties via de webbrowser ter beschikking stelt van gebruikers, laat Amazon toe om in enkele seconden een (bijna) ongelimiteerd aantal servers, in de vorm van virtuele machines, op te starten en te beheren. Daarbij maakt het gebruik van een pay-as-you-go model: je betaalt enkel voor de tijd dat je servers draaien.</p>\r\n<p>Naast Amazon zijn er nog een groot aantal andere IaaS providers momenteel actief. Allen bieden ze meerdere instance types &ndash;configuraties van virtuele machines (aantal CPU&rsquo;s, snelheid van CPU, hoeveelheid RAM-geheugen, harde schijf-ruimte, platform, I/O performance&hellip;)&ndash; aan tegen verschillende kost. Daarnaast biedt o.a. Amazon ook &ldquo;load balancing&rdquo;-features aan: wanneer de load in een virtuele machine te hoog wordt, kan er automatisch beslist worden om een extra server op te starten.</p>\r\n<p>De keuze voor een bepaald instance type is echter niet triviaal: er moet rekening gehouden worden met de specifieke karakteristieken van de applicatie. Doel van de thesis is het scheppen van een algemeen kader dat hulp biedt bij het maken van deze keuze. Daarbij zullen een aantal metrics bepaald moeten worden die toelaten applicaties categoriseren in bijvoorbeeld computationele, netwerk-intensieve of data-intensieve taken. Voorts zullen deze karakteristieken gemapt&nbsp; worden op de statische eigenschappen en/of benchmarks van de verschillende instance types en providers. Ook moet de horizontale schaalbaarheid van de applicatie bepaald kunnen worden, zodat een afweging gemaakt kan worden tussen een horizontale schaling (i.e. meerdere servers) en een verticale schaling (i.e. meer CPU&rsquo;s/meer geheugen/&hellip;). Naast een algemeen kader, dat in principe alle soorten applicaties omvat, zullen er bij wijze van demonstratie ook een aantal concrete applicaties ge&euml;valueerd dienen te worden.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Amazon EC2 Instance types: http://aws.amazon.com/ec2/instance-types/</li>\r\n</ul>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'A Market Design for IaaS Cloud Resources','<p>IaaS clouds deliver infrastructure level-resources (processing power, memory, data storage, networking) as a commodity to clients through an on-demand and pay-per-use model [1]. At present, the model for trading cloud resources at the major providers (Amazon, Microsoft, Rightscale), involves the provider defining its own trading mechanism. Amazon for example [2], currently one of the most successful IaaS providers, sells its cloud resources through a spot market with prices that vary based on supply and demand during the week, through a reservation-based market with fixed prices, and through a fixed pricing scheme for non-reserved resources. </p>\n\n<p>The commoditization of IT resources brought forth by the IaaS paradigm eases the deployment and management of applications on third party remote resources significantly. It also increases the possibilities for trading IaaS resources on a scale that moves beyond the individual provider level. Such inter-provider trading is used in other commodities markets such as electricity markets, to efficiently balance supply and demand on relatively short timescales. In addition, an open market for IaaS resources can efficiently open up the cloud IaaS provider space to less dedicated resources such as pools of desktop machines which represent a huge potential pool of processing power. </p>\n\n<p>At present however, the possibilities for creating such open markets for IaaS resources have been largely unexplored. The goal of this thesis is to investigate:\n1) Whether it is theoretically feasible to design an open market for cloud resources\n2) The design options for open IaaS markets. In this respect, you will also look into the design of markets for energy trading and evaluate the differences and parallels with IaaS markets. \n3) The behavior of the proposed market design in terms of price formation and stability through simulation </p>\n\n<p>[1] M. Armbrust et. al,  Above the Clouds: A Berkeley View of Cloud Computing, Armbrust et al., EECS Department, University of California, Berkeley, 2009, http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Pubs/TechRpts/2009/EECS-2009-28.html \n[2] Amazon, LLC, Amazon EC2 Pricing http://aws.amazon.com/ec2/pricing/\n[3] N. Dube, Supercomputing futures the Next Sharing Paradigm for HPC Resources, http://www.nic.qc.ca/files/nicdube<em>PhD</em>thesis.pdf</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'A Broker for Cost-efficient QoS aware resource allocation in EC2','<p>Amazon\'s Elastic Compute Service (EC2) [1] cloud offering [2] allows consumers to allocate virtual machine instances, that run a user-defined operating system and application software stack, in its datacenters in an on-demand fashion. That is, a user has the ability to allocate or deallocate virtual machine instances at any time according to the its workload demand. </p>\n\n<p>In terms of pricing, a user has the option [3]: \n1) To allocate instances on a spot market with prices that vary hourly. Instances can be shut down by EC2 if the consumer\'s bid no longer exceeds the spot market price. \n2) To buy reserved instances with a guaranteed availability. This requires an upfront payment for an instance for a one or three year period, supplemented with usage based pricing based on a fixed price.\n3) To allocate on-demand instances that are priced with a fixed charging rate. Once launched, these instances are guaranteed to be kept live as long as the user pays for them. In principle, a user does not have a full guarantee of being able to launch a (set of) on-demand instance(s) </p>\n\n<p>At present, consumers do not have any tools to optimally map their workload and QoS requirements (such as the deadline by a which a workload needs to finish), to these different pricing plans. Nevertheless the potential for cost reductions through intelligent instance allocations are huge (a small EC2 instance allocated on the spot market for example has a cost which is, on average, about 50% below the current cost for an on-demand instance [4]). </p>\n\n<p>The goal of this thesis is to devise heuristics that can be used by a brokering component to realize this optimization goal. This involves an analysis of the consumer\'s workload characteristics (baseline workload level, demand surge patterns, checkpointing costs, ...), QoS requirements and the volatility of the EC2 spot market to define an optimal portfolio of instance allocations across the three pricing plans. </p>\n\n<p>[1] Amazon, LLC, Amazon EC2 http://aws.amazon.com/ec2/<br>\n[2] M. Armbrust et. al,  Above the Clouds: A Berkeley View of Cloud Computing, Armbrust et al., EECS Department, University of California, Berkeley, 2009, http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Pubs/TechRpts/2009/EECS-2009-28.html <br>\n[3] Amazon, LLC, Amazon EC2 http://aws.amazon.com/ec2/<br>\n[4] Cloud Exchange, http://cloudexchange.org/</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Dynamic Pricing for Desktop Clouds','<p>Since the conception of the SETI@home project, voluntueer computing projects have enjoyed a continuous growth over the years. The general-purpose BOINC desktop computing grid now averages about 5.1 petaflops, the more application specific Folding@home sustains over 6.2 petaflops. Nevertheless only a fraction of the available desktop processing power available on the internet is nowadays being harvested. This is partly due to the fact that, at present, the donation of resources to desktop grid projects are done on a voluntary basis. With the introduction of the cloud computing paradigm, a piecewise delivery and payment model for IT resources is rapidly gaining interest and acceptance. Consequently, there currently exist an opportunity for creating an economic incentive to integrate cycles into a so called \"desktop cloud\". </p>\n\n<p>The goal of this research internship is to investigate the technical challenges for realizing such a desktop cloud model and to explore the design of a market mechanism that allows one to link up pools of desktop grid resources across the internet, and price their use dynamically based on supply and demand. A key challenge in this regard is the scale at which the system needs to operate, and to incorporate the varying availability desktop resources in the pricing mechanism. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Het toevoegen van een forum structuur in de chaos van mailing lists','<p>Mailing lists laten toe om met een groep van mensen te communiceren en worden vaak gebruikt in de open source en academische wereld. Deze manier van communiceren is echter verre van perfect doordat mailing lists bovenop e-mail gebouwd zijn. Het voornaamste probleem is een gebrek aan structuur: Een conversatie zit namelijk verscholen in een hele resem van e-mails. Je moet ze allemaal &eacute;&eacute;n voor &eacute;&eacute;n in de juiste volgorde lezen om te trachten een overzicht van de conversatie te krijgen.</p>\r\n<p>Het doel van dit project is dit probleem op te lossen door structuur toe te voegen aan mailing lists. Dit kan gebeuren door een gebruikersinterface te bouwen die werkt met bestaande mailing lists, maar waar de onderliggende e-mail infrastructuur weggeabstraheerd wordt. Qua structuur kan er inspiratie gehaald worden bij internet forums: Elke conversatie is hier een aparte thread/topic die behoort tot een bepaalde categorie/subforum. Zo\'n forum structuur maakt het al veel makkelijker om een duidelijk overzicht te krijgen van de conversaties zelf, en welke conversaties er allemaal zijn. In dit project zal dus een gebruikersinterface gebouwd worden zodanig dat mailing lists op een gelijkaardige manier als een forum gebruikt kunnen worden. Een voordeel van mailing lists tegenover forums is dat ze ingebouwd zitten in je e-mail client. (De gebruikersinterface van elke mailing list is steeds dezelfde; je kan deze interface ook naar wens aanpassen; je krijgt automatisch notifications van nieuwe berichten; ...) Om die reden wordt dit project bij voorkeur uitgewerkt als een plug-in/add-on voor een bestaande e-mail client. Aangezien Mozilla producten gekend zijn om hun focus op add-ons is de Mozilla Thunderbird e-mail client een geschikte kandidaat.</p>\r\n<p>Dit project is interessant omdat:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Je leert werken met een bestaand platform, zijnde Mozilla Thunderbird.</li>\r\n<li>Het project is nuttig voor vele mailing list gebruikers.</li>\r\n<li>Het project kan verder leven in een open-source community, zoals Sourceforge of Google Code.</li>\r\n<li>Er is samenwerking mogelijk met gerelateerde ESP projecten \"Toegang tot vBulletin/phpBB forums vanuit Mozilla Thunderbird\" en \"Building a unified user interface for internet forums using pattern recognition\".</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Meer informatie omtrent de omliggende context van dit project is te bekijken in volgende presentatie: <a href=\"http://win.ua.ac.be/~tmolder/documents/ForumsAndMailingLists.pdf\">.pdf</a> (Slide 12 speelt in op dit specifieke project.)</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Recognition of COBOL Control-Flow Patterns and Mapping to  OO-Constructs [with industrial partner]','<p><a href=\"http://www.anubex.com/\">Anubex</a> is an internationally recognized leader in the domain of automated software reengineering and its use in large-scale application modernization projects. From its headquarters in Kontich, Belgium, Anubex conducts several software and data migrations at any moment in time for the world&rsquo;s most prestigious companies and government institutions. Anubex invests continually in the research and development of new tools and techniques to extend the boundaries and improve the quality of its service.</p>\r\n<p>The objective of this project is an exhaustive study of control-flow patterns as they appear in real-world COBOL programs and their mappings to the type of constructs available in modern OO-languages like Java or C#.</p>\r\n<p>With control-flow patterns, we mean combinations of multi-statement constructs that convey a certain well-established meaning. As an example, COBOL programs often make use of GOTO statements for reaching a common exit-point in case of error conditions. This specific use of the GOTO statement could be recognized and mapped to the use of Exceptions in an OO-language.</p>\r\n<p>The research project should focus on the discovery and/or automated recognition of these control-flow patterns in a large body of real-world COBOL applications. Based on this catalog of recognized patterns, a second (part of the) project should formulate approaches to mapping these patterns to constructs in an OO-language.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Mapping COBOL Data Types OO-Constructs  [industrial partner]','<p><a href=\"http://www.anubex.com/\">Anubex</a> is an internationally recognized leader in the domain of automated software reengineering and its use in large-scale application modernization projects. From its headquarters in Kontich, Belgium, Anubex conducts several software and data migrations at any moment in time for the world&rsquo;s most prestigious companies and government institutions. Anubex invests continually in the research and development of new tools and techniques to extend the boundaries and improve the quality of its service.</p>\r\n<p>This project will deal with data-types in COBOL and modern OO-languages like Java or C#. The first objective is to compare the representation and use of data types in these languages and document their major differences. Based on this understanding, approaches to the (automated) conversion of COBOL data-types to Java/C# data-types should be formulated and compared.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Implementing a virtual network architecture using XMPP','<p>Uit Jabber dat vooral gericht was om IM diensten te implementeren is het Extensible Messaging and Presence Protocol gegroeid dat zich uitbreidt naar bericht-georinteerde middleware. Door de grote beschikbaarheid van XMPP gerelateerde software (libraries), de generische architectuur, de mogelijkheid om firewalls via HTTP te omzeilen is XMPP uitgegroeid tot meer dan een IM service. </p>\n\n<p>Binnen PATS zien we met de mogelijkheid om XMPP als een transport en authenticatie middel om een virtueel netwerk op te bouwen bestaande uit toestellen verbonden op een reel netwerk.</p>\n\n<p>Een mogelijke applicatie kan zijn om verschillende geografisch verspreide (private) netwerken te monitoren (status, uptime, statistics) en te beheren (update, configuratie, reboot, etc.) via een virtueel controle netwerk.</p>\n\n<p>We verwachten van de student dat hij/zij op zelfstandige basis op zoek gaat naar de nodige tools (XMPP server, XMPP client library). De uiteindelijk keuze wordt gemaakt in samenwerking met de begeleider. De bedoeling is daarna een testopstelling (al dan niet permanent) uit te werken die kan gebruikt worden om verschillende strategien te testen, te evalueren (performantie-evaluatie) en te vergelijken. Als het interessant wordt bevonden kan er ook een vergelijking worden gemaakt met bestaande oplossingen voor dit probleem.</p>\n\n<p>Een aantal interessante links</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://xmpp.org/\">http://xmpp.org/</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://socialvpn.wordpress.com/\">http://socialvpn.wordpress.com/</a></li>\n</ul>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Unifying Modelica and Meta-Modelling','<p>The language <a href=\"http://www.modelica.org\">Modelica</a> allows for acausal, object-oriented modelling of physical systems. Acausal refers to the ability to describe declarative (implicit) equations. A Modelica compiler assigns computational causality and \"flattens\" object-oriented constructs. Modelica has attracted a large following over the last decade, especially in the automotive world. To allow elegant (rule-based) transformation of Modelica models as well as the construction of (visual) domain-specific modelling environments, a Modelica compiler based on a Meta-Modelling kernel is proposed. The thesis will develop a Modelica compiler front-end based on the \nOpen Source <a href=\"http://www.openmodelica.org/\">openModelica</a> compiler. The target back-end will however be graph-based.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Statechart synthesis of SVG/Ajax Web user interfaces','<p>There are many challenges that developers face during the development\nof a complex User Interface (UI). Desired behaviour may be autonomous\nor reactive, and possibly real-time. Each UI component may be\nrequired to exhibit a radically different behaviour from that of any\nother component and the behaviour of components may be inter-related.\nThese complex behavioural relationships between components are often\ndifficult to express, and are even more difficult to encode and\nmaintain.</p>\n\n<p>There are also difficulties related to the development process: the\ndeveloper must be able to rapidly adapt the structure and behaviour of\nthe UI to changing system requirements. Unfortunately, conventional\ncode-centric approaches fall short. We suggest that a developer\nshould specify the behaviour of a UI using a representation which\nminimizes \"accidental complexity\".</p>\n\n<p>Our solution uses Model-Driven Engineering (MDE). By modelling every\naspect of the system-to-be-built, at the most appropriate level of\nabstraction, using the most appropriate formalism(s), it becomes\npossible to completely capture the behaviour of a UI, to rapidly\ngenerate prototype implementations, to easily adapt the UI as project\nrequirements change, and, finally, to synthesize a UI and maintain it.</p>\n\n<p>More specifically, this thesis will investigate a class of UIs known as\nScoped User Interfaces, and in particular, how one may model them using\nHierarchically-linked Statecharts (HlS). A Scoped User Interface is\none in which reactive visual components (widgets) such as buttons and\nwindows are hierarchically nested. <a href=\"http://portal.acm.org/citation.cfm?doid=42411.42414\">Statecharts</a> \nis a modelling formalism initially proposed by David Harel as an extension of Finite\nState Machines. It was intended as a solution for modelling complex,\nstate-based behaviour, and is now included as a part of the OMG\nUnified Modeling Language (OMG UML) Superstructure specification. HlS\napplies an actor-based approach to modelling the behaviour of UIs,\nexplicitly modelling each hierarchically-scoped UI component. A\ndefault event model that implements hierarchical event capturing and\nbubbling is used to bind the system together, and allows widgets at\nthe highest level of the hierarchy to exhibit a general behaviour,\nwhile widgets deeper in the hierarchy exhibit more specific behaviour.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.w3.org/Graphics/SVG/About\">Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG)</a> \nprovides a complete platform for the development of such applications.\nBecause SVG supports scripting interactivity, it is possible<br>\nto bind each Statechart instance\nto a newly-created, SVG-based widget, with minimal \"glue\" code. The\nSVG DOM is inherently hierarchical, and can hence be used to encode\nhierarchical relationships between UI components. The SVG event model\nthen, enables the hierarchical event handling for arbitrarily\ncomplex, dynamically created widgets. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Epsilon Object Language compiler','<p><a href=\"http://www.eclipse.org/gmt/epsilon/\">Epsilon</a> is a family of consistent and\ninteroperable task-specific programming languages which you\ncan use to interact with models to perform common Model Driven Engineering tasks such as\ncode generation, model-to-model transformation, model validation, comparison,\nmigration, merging and refactoring.\nThe <a href=\"http://www.eclipse.org/gmt/epsilon/doc/eol/\">Epsilon Object Language (EOL)</a>\nEOL is an imperative programming language (also known as \"action language\")\nfor creating, querying and modifying\n<a href=\"http://www.eclipse.org/modeling/emf/\">Eclipse Modelling Framework (EMF)</a> models.\nYou can think of it as a mixture of Javascript and OCL, combining the best of both worlds.\nAs such, it provides all the usual imperative features found in Javascript (e.g.,\nstatement sequencing, variables, for and while loops, if branches etc.)\nand all the nice features of OCL such as those handy collection querying functions (e.g., <code>Sequence{1..5}.select(x|x&gt;3)</code>).</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Web-based text editor for Writing research','<p>The use of computers as writing instruments has not only had a profound effect on\nwriting practice, but has also opened up new possibilities for writing research. \nResearchers make frequent use of keystroke logging tools to describe the online writing processes in detail.\nThe tool <a href=\"http://www.inputlog.net/\">inputlog</a> was developed by\nProf. <a href=\"http://webhost.ua.ac.be/lvanwaes/index.html\">Luuk Van Waes</a> and his team\nto conduct extremely fine-grained studies of the time course of writing processes.\nIt is an input logging tool that logs all input modes: keyboard, mouse and speech.\nThe purpose of this thesis is to develop, based on good software engineering principles,\nan object-oriented design of a web-based Rich Text editor (zoals <a href=\"http://docs.google.com\">Google Docs</a>).\nIn particular, the design will be based on the Gang of Four Design Pattern book.\nThe design is complemented by a series of prototype implementations using <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ECMAScript\">ECSMAScript</a>\nand <a href=\"http://www.w3.org/Graphics/SVG/About\">Scalable Vector Graphics (SVG)</a>.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Business Process Modelling','<p>Modelling languages such as the <a href=\"http://www.bpmn.org/\">Business Process Modeling Notation (BPMN)</a> \nand <a href=\"http://www.yawlfoundation.org/\">YAWL:Yet Another Workflow Language</a> allow business to\nexplicitly (and graphically) model their business procedures and communicate them in a standard manner. \nThis thesis compares different modelling languages and investigates and implements analyses (for example,\nby mapping onto Petri Nets) and simulations (for example, by mapping onto the DEVS discrete-event\nsimulation language) that can be performed.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Petri Net analysis','<p>Petri Nets allow for concise representation of non-deterministic, concurrent behaviour.\nPetri Nets can be analyzed through either the construction of a reachability/coverability graph\nor through matrix-based techniques. This thesis develops a usable and scale-able\nPetri Net analysis tool within the <a href=\"http://atom3.cs.mcgill.ca/\">AToM^3</a>  environment.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Meta-Modelling and Transformation Environment','<p><a href=\"http://atom3.cs.mcgill.ca\">(AToM^3) A Tool for Multi-formalism and Meta-Modelling</a>\nhas been under development since 2001. A complete re-write of the kernel is currently\nin progress. This thesis will use the current AToM^3 modelling environment to\nprovide a visual interface to this new kernel. The focus will be on the synthesis of\na modelling and execution environment for (higher-order) model transformation.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Model Differencing','<p>To bring Model Driven Engineering to the level of an engineering discipline,\nfeatures known from Software Engineering must be supported. In particular, it\nmust be possible to compare models. This \"diff-ing\" forms the basis for many\nhigher-level features such as version control. As models are inherently graph-like,\nmodel comparison can no longer be based on string comparison. This thesis\ninvestigates different model differencing approaches in the context of MDE and\nconstructs a prototype implementation.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Mapping transformation rules onto database queries','<p>Rule-based specifications of model transformations are easy to understand and maintain. They are traditionally compiled to algorithms which use Create/Read/Update/Delete (CRUD) operations on models, in memory. As Model-Driven Engineering (MDE) gains importance, the size of models keeps increasing. When extremely large, graph-like models (i.e., millions of nodes and edges) are used, they no longer fit in memory. This thesis builds on early work by Daniel Varro and investigates the compilation of rules to database operations.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Empowering knowledge computing with variable selection (for regression)','<p>Empowering knowledge computing with variable selection (for regression) by Katya Vladislavleva</p>\n\n<p>Variable selection is a process of identifying influential variables (attributes) in a real or simulated system, that are discriminative and necessary to describe the system performance characteristics.</p>\n\n<p>Focusing the research  (and modeling) on relevant variables reduces the dimensionality of the original problem (by making the problem tractable), shortens time to market (by facilitating insights), improves generalization (by generating robust knowledge), and heavily cuts down the costs on product design.</p>\n\n<p>In the current era of \"Data, Data Everywhere\" scientists are observing information explosion and understanding implosion. This makes computational modeling and knowledge computing necessary, and crucial skill demanded by every scientist. </p>\n\n<p>Data-driven Knowledge computing is impossible without proper variable selection, which makes variable selection such a \'hot topic\' these days. Many books are written and are being written on variable selection in Machine Learning, Data Mining and Artificial intelligence, but the absolute majority of them is focused on deriving relevant variables from classification problems. Variable selection for regression problems, where important control variables can take arbitrary numeric values (not necessarily from a fixed set of classes) - is a lot more applicable problem, but it <em>significantly</em> harder and less understood. </p>\n\n<p>Deterministic statistical methods for variable selection for regression are not scalable to large data sets, and produce bad-quality models, which are supposed to reliably relate relevant data variables with each other and with important control variables (outputs) (see, for example [2]).</p>\n\n<p>A successful stochastic heuristic using random forests [3] can be made very efficient, but it\'s models also lack transparency and analyticity. </p>\n\n<p>Intelligently designed hybrid neural networks [4], and symbolic regression via genetic programming [6] are the two most promising methodologies for variable selection for regression (see e.g. [5],[7]). The first one is efficient, but produces black-box models, the second one requires more time, but produces reliable analytic \"white-box\" models. </p>\n\n<p>The proposed project will aim at combining the best features of the relevant methodologies to create an effective, efficient, and robust intelligent system for variable selection for regression. </p>\n\n<p>I am looking for two to three motivated Master students who are creative, adventurous, have analytic minds, exquisite programming skills and strong interest to the practical applications of knowledge computing and computational intelligence. <em>The projects can be done individually (on different topics of variable selection) or in a group (with explicitly defined priorities for each team member).</em></p>\n\n<p>To complete this project we will not only have to develop such a variable selection system, but also critically access it\'s limitations (e.g. characterize the data sets where the variable selection will not be tractable). The less limitations - the better. </p>\n\n<p>[1] Data, data everywhere - A special report on managing information. URL:http://www.economist.com/specialreports/displaystory.cfm?story_id=15557443 </p>\n\n<p>[2] http://www.geniq.net/res/variable-selection-methods-produce-bad-models.html</p>\n\n<p>[3] http://www.stat.berkeley.edu/~breiman/RandomForests/</p>\n\n<p>[4] Empirical models with self-accessment capabilities for online industrial applications by A. Kordon, G. Smits, E. Jordaan, A. Kalos, and L. Chiang. 2006 </p>\n\n<p>[5] Variable selection in industrial datasets using Pareto genetic programming by G. Smits, A. Kordon, K.Vladislavleva, E. Jordaan, M.Kotanchek. 2005</p>\n\n<p>[6] Model-based problem solving with Symbolic Regression via Pareto genetic programming by E. Vladislavleva. 2008</p>\n\n<p>[7] Knowlege mining with GP methods for variable selection in flavor design by K. Vladislavleva, K. Veeramachaneni, M. Burland, J. Parcon, and U.-M. O\'Reilly 2010</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Link prediction in text','<p>Het doel van dit project is om efficiente algoritmen voor link predictie te ontwerpen voor grote gelinkte datasets, zoals bijvoorbeeld Wikipedia. De huidige methoden voor link predictie gebruiken of de textual\n similarity tussen documenten om links te voorspellen of de structuur v/d al aanwezige links in de document collectie.  In dit project willen we beide gebruiken, waarbij de similarity tussen twee documenten een waarde geeft over hoe betrouwbaar de link tussen deze documenten is. Voor link predictie op basis v/d link structuur kan gebruik worden gemaakt van bestaande technieken zoals vb. random walks with restarts. Voor het bepalen v/h gewicht van een link kan gebruik worden gemaakt van IR technieken zoals, word co occurrence, google distance, cosine similarity. Verder moet er een uitgebreide experimentele evaluatie worden gedaan tussen de verschillende  zienswijzen.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Cluster implementatie van OpenCL','<p>OpenCL (Open Computing Language) is a framework for writing programs that execute across \nheterogeneous  platforms consisting of CPUs, GPUs, and other processors. OpenCL provides a language that is based on the C language (C99), supplemented by APIs enabling task-based and data-based parallelism. </p>\n\n<p>Writing parallel software using the OpenCL framework is advantageous because (1) it forces the designers to rethink the problems and design new parallel algorithms, (2) it hides the complexity inherent in the hardware and software for distributing the code on the available resources, and (3) it makes the software written in this framework is device-independent</p>\n\n<p>While the OpenCL computing framework is very promising, currently only implementations for GPU\'s or CPU\'s residing on a single machine are available. A single CPU is clearly not powerful enough for advanced applications, and not all applications are suited for computation on a GPU. To have more computing power available and to not be limited by current GPU hardware, OpenCL must be extended to compute clusters.</p>\n\n<p>The goal of this master thesis is to design, implement, test and benchmark an OpenCL framework for compute clusters.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'RAFT Services','<p>A well known parallel algorithm is the so-called farmer-worker or master-worker algorithm.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>An improved version of this algorithm was developed a few years ago and is described in full detail <a href=\"http://win.ua.ac.be/~vincenz/hpcn97.pdf\">here</a>. The improvement, allows load balancing and higher reliability to be achieved. Its general structure is concisely described in the following picture:</p>\r\n<center><img src=\"http://win.ua.ac.be/~vincenz/schema.gif\" alt=\"\" /></center>\r\n<p>This algorithm was then implemented for clusters of workstation with the MPICH implementation of MPI. The corresponding package, RAFTNET (that is Reliable And Fault Tolerant Network), is available <a href=\"http://sourceforge.net/projects/raftnet/\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>We would like to redesign RAFTNET so as to</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Allow a variable number of worker <em>services</em>to be dynamically orchestrated.</li>\r\n<li>Select the workers according to adaptive quality requirements (e.g., performance, or minimal reliability requirements).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Furthermore we would like to analyze the performability of the new system and publish results in the form of a conference paper.</p>\r\n<p>For this project students are expected to be able to design and develop service oriented architectures.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Performance of Random Access Systems','<p>The objective of this thesis exists in assessing the performance of various random access algorithms via analytical methods. The methods considered include branching processes, Markov chain modeling, etc. Models with both finite and infinite populations will be considered, while the main performance measures include the maximum stable throughput, the mean delay and the energy consumption of the algorithm.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Netwerkbeveiliging door het combineren van beveiligingstechnieken');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Cartification');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Pattern Set Mining','<p>In this thesis, you will study general techniques for mining sets of patterns directly. Such pattern sets should contain only high quality patterns that are of direct interest to the user and her application. As such this study constitutes an attempt to answer one of the most important open research questions of the field of pattern mining. The set of frequent patterns derived by most of the current pattern mining methods is too huge for effective usage. Much research is still needed to substantially reduce the size of derived pattern sets and enhance the quality of retained patterns.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Dependability Analysis of WSDM-enabled Web Services','<p>Grote gedistribueerde enterprise software wordt hoe langer hoe meer gestructureerd in de vorm van Service-Oriented Architectures (SOA&rsquo;s), waarbij bestaande softwarecomponenten gewrapt worden in XML-gebaseerde web services. In feite omvat het SOA-paradigma de best practices van gedistribueerd programmeren van ruwweg de voorbije twintig jaar en commercieel ondersteund door bedrijven blijft SOA in populariteit toenemen.</p>\r\n<p>Het doel van deze thesis is een zo goed mogelijke inschatting te bekomen van het prestatievermogen van web services (QoS), met bijzondere aandacht voor dependability aspecten. Hiervoor kunnen zowel functionele als niet-functionele aspecten van services beschouwd worden. De WSDM-specificatie (Web Services Distributed Management) is een OASIS-standaard die vastlegt hoe je zulke eigenschappen kan meten en observeren. Het Apache MUSE project is een generieke softwarebibliotheek die de gebruiker in staat stelt web services conform deze WSDM-specificatie te ontwikkelen en te hosten op Java applicatieservers zoals Tomcat of Glassfish, of zelfs op mobiele devices m.b.v. technologie&euml;n zoals OSGi.</p>\r\n<p>Je kan gebruik kunnen maken van een bestaand framework voor reflective and refractive variables op basis van Apache MUSE. Naast de variabelen die in de MOWS-specificatie gedefinieerd zijn, kunnen applicatie-specifieke eigenschappen van een managed web service in de WSDL-interface beschikbaar gesteld worden. Je gebruikt de MOWS-metrieken en een afschatting van de service reliability om in functie van de systeemstatus evenwichtig de load te balanceren tussen de beschikbare services in het systeem en te detecteren wanneer er nieuwe replica&rsquo;s van een bepaalde service aan het systeem toegevoegd moeten worden. <strong>Concreet implementeer je generische softwarecomponenten voor fouttolerante technieken zoals NVP, RB en rejuvination en onderzoek je de impact van de geobserveerde metrieken op het aantal service replica&rsquo;s dat noodzakelijk is om het prestatievermogen van de dependability strategy te maximaliseren</strong> (i.f.v. uitvoeringstijd, hoeveelheid resources, fault resilience etc.). Je zult begeleid worden om een aantal academische publicaties te lezen over fouttolerantie die je in staat zullen stellen om de vereiste technieken te kaderen en te implementeren in de globale architectuur van een RAFTnet (zie figuur).</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.win.ua.ac.be/~vincenz/raftnet.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Vervolgens onderzoek je hoe je op remote hosts nieuwe service replica&rsquo;s kan alloceren</strong>. Aangezien klassieke J2EE application servers dit technisch niet ondersteunen, impliceert dit dat voor het volledige project een (r-)OSGI runtime als hosting platform noodzakelijk is. Voor dit deel van het project zal je ervoor moeten zorgen dat je MUSE-services kan draaien op een recente versie van Eclipse Equinox, en experimenteer je met bvb. de CDC/FP1.1 OSGi runtime van ProSyst op mobile devices.</p>\r\n<p>Als sluitstuk bestudeer je de haalbaarheid om <strong>WS-Policy te gebruiken voor foutdetectie</strong>. Op basis van de bestaande WS-Policy implementatie, Apache Neethi, zoek je een oplossing hoe je at runtime WS-Policy constraints kan afdwingen en controleren in MUSE. In het bijzonder ontwerp en implementeer je een oplossing die toelaat de enforcement van policies in Apache Axis2 gedeeltelijk uit te voeren, en waarbij applicatie-specifieke policies in MUSE gecontroleerd worden.</p>\r\n<p>Voorkennis: Een grondig begrip van XML en XML Schema (XSD) is noodzakelijk. Toepassen van software design patterns tijdens de implementatie is een pluspunt. Mogelijk kan je een basiskennis putten uit de vakken Gedistribueerde Systemen en/of Distributed Computing Paradigms uit de eerste master.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Logisim naar Verilog vertaler','<p>De Logisim omgeving laat toe logische circuits visueel te modelleren en te simuleren. De Verilog taal laat toe logische circuits textueel te beschrijven en te simuleren (bijvoorbeeld met behulp van de Icarus Verilog compiler). Verilog wordt, samen met VHDL, industrieel gebruikt en laat toe heel complexe systemen efficient te simuleren.<br>\nDit project bouwt een vertaler van Logisim modellen naar hun Verilog voorstelling. De vertaling bestaat uit een omzetting van enerzijds de connectietopologie en van anderzijds de Verilog basisbouwblokken naar equivalente bouwblokken uit de Verilog standaardbibliotheek.<br>\nVerilog biedt uitgebreide faciliteiten voor het beschrijven van simulatie-experimenten (en het automatisch uitvoeren van testen).  Met behulp van deze vertaler wordt het dan ook mogelijk van automatisch Logisim modellen te testen op correctheid.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'FPGA implementatie van een Logisim ontwerp','<p>Dit project ontwikkelt de MIPS-achtige architectuur uit de oefeningen verder.<br>\nDit ontwerp wordt dan manueel omgezet naar een speficicatie die kan gebruikt worden door een \"silicon compiler\". Deze zet de specificatie om naar hardware op een FPGA (\"Field Programmable Gate Array\").<br>\nHet hardware gedeelte van dit werk gebeurt op de Karel de Grote hogeschool.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Ontwerp en implementatie van een software applicatie voor codificatie van medische ingrepen');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Opslag van patint-monitoring gegevens voor wetenschappelijk onderzoek','<p>Naast de afdeling intensieve zorgen, worden ook op een aantal verpleegkundige afdelingen in het Universitair Ziekenhuis Antwerpen patinten actief opgevolgd via elektronische monitoring systemen. Een aantal parameters zoals hartslag, bloeddruk en zuurstofsaturatie worden daarbij gemeten. Indien deze parameters buiten vooraf ingestelde grenswaarden gaan, gaan alarmen af en wordt een verpleegster automatisch gewaarschuwd zodat de patint snel de juiste zorg toegediend krijgt. Voor wetenschappelijk onderzoek wensen we nog een stap verder te gaan dan louter monitoring van deze gegevens en alarmering. Daarom zal een systeem ontworpen worden dat deze gegevens efficint opslaat zodat ze bruikbaar worden voor wetenschappelijke onderzoeksdoeleinden.</p>\n\n<p>Dit eindwerk omvat het onderzoeken en opzetten van een volledig systeem voor het opslaan van deze gegevens en het toegankelijk maken ervan voor wetenschappelijk onderzoek. De gegevens worden opgevangen via een standaard uitwisselingsprotocol voor medische gegevens, namelijk via HL7 berichten. Aan de hand van dit protocol dient een efficinte databank structuur te worden opgezet om deze gegevens in op te slaan, daarbij rekening houdend met een aantal factoren zoals opslagcapaciteit en efficinte bevraagbaarheid naar wetenschappelijk onderzoek.</p>\n\n<p>In het eindwerk zal allereerst een analyse gemaakt worden van het probleem en zal er vervolgens een volledige architectuur voorgesteld worden om de gegevens op te slaan. Een database structuur wordt opgesteld en gekoppeld aan de monitoring systemen door middel van het uitwisselen van HL7 berichten. Mogelijk dient daarbij lossy/lossless wavelet-compressie gebruikt te worden om de signalen te kunnen opslaan. Finaal zal ook een evaluatie gemaakt worden van de algemene efficintie en bruikbaarheid van de geboden oplossing. Eigen initiatief en input worden sterk aangemoedigd en kunnen het project ook in belangrijke mate sturen.</p>\n\n<p>Voorkennis: </p>\n\n<p>initiatiefnemer met brede interesse (medisch, algoritmisch), kennis van relationele database systemen en programmeerervaring (bvb. Java)</p>\n\n<p>Contact: tim.van.den.bulcke@uza.be</p>\n\n<p>Referenties:</p>\n\n<p> UZA: http://www.uza.be\n HL7: http://www.hl7.org/\n Monitoring: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical<em>monitor\n Wavelet transforms: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wavelet</em>Transform</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Evaluatie van algoritmes voor de-identificatie van elektronische patintendossiers','<p>Elektronische patintendossiers (EPDs) bevatten een grote hoeveelheid informatie die als vrije tekst beschreven staat. Die informatie is zeer waardevol voor wetenschappelijk onderzoek dat de diagnose en behandeling van patinten ten goede kan komen. Niettemin is dit ook zeer gevoelige informatie aangezien de vrije tekst gegevens kan bevatten die de identiteit van de patint rechtstreeks of onrechtstreeks kunnen onthullen.</p>\n\n<p>De bescherming van de privacy van patinten is cruciaal. Elektronische patintendossiers anonimiseren gaat veel verder dan het verwijderen van contactgegevens uit de dossiers en omvat onder andere: 1) het verwijderen van namen, telefoonnummers, plaatsen uit artsenverslagen; 2) het randomizeren van geboorte- en andere data zonder verlies aan informatie; 3) het identificeren en anomimiseren van meer contextuele informatie.</p>\n\n<p>In dit eindwerk zal je een evaluatie maken van bestaande de-identificatie software aan de hand van een aantal metrieken op zowel publieke gegevens als op een beperkte corpus van ziekenhuisgegevens die je samenstelt gedurende het eindwerk.</p>\n\n<p>Contact: tim.van.den.bulcke@uza.be</p>\n\n<p>Referenties:</p>\n\n<p> http://www.physionet.org/physiotools/deid/\n http://www.clarin.eu/tools/csts-lemmatizer</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Exploring the state-of-the-art in SOA security','<p>Over the years, large enterprises have accumulated a diversity of heterogeneous software systems. However, this heterogeneity imposes limitations on composing and orchestrating such existing legacy IT assets (such as databases, technology-specific software systems, mainframe applications) into more complex services. In the beginning of this decade, this issue led to the concept of service-oriented architectures (SOA) in which IT is flexibly structured by splitting up the business logic in a number of software components that are exposed as services with explicit, platform-neutral interfaces. Actually this service-oriented computing paradigm comprises the best practices in distributed computing of &ndash; roughly estimated &ndash; the past twenty years, and commercially backed by major industry concerns, SOA continues to gain in popularity. As one possible SOA implementation technology, XML-based web services have managed to become the de facto standard for distributed enterprise applications.</p>\r\n<p>However, existing point-to-point security technologies such as SSL are no longer adequate to enforce security in distributed systems [1, 2]. The <a href=\"http://www.soaspecs.com/ws-security.php\">WS-Security framework</a>, a framework to secure data at application level, was conceived to protect the exchanged data between web services in order to prevent their misuse.</p>\r\n<p>The Extensible Messaging and Presence (XMPP) protocol, which is used as a transport for iChat, GoogleTalk and other Jabber services, initially emerged as message-oriented middleware. In spite of the powerful features offered by WS-Security, securing data at application level may to some extent degrade system performance. Within PATS, we are interested in leveraging the XMPP transport and security mechanisms [3] and combining these features with those in WS-Security.</p>\r\n<p>The aim of this thesis is to compare the WS-Security and XMPP specifications with respect to the five security aspects (identification, authentication, authorization, integrity and confidentiality), finding the overlaps and subsequently assess how well either of the alternatives performs to secure web services interaction.</p>\r\n<p>For this thesis, you will be able to use powerful open-source software such as <a href=\"http://ws.apache.org/axis2\">Apache Axis2</a> and <a href=\"http://ws.apache.org/rampart\">Apache Rampart</a>. Relevant academic publications will be selected and the supervisors will introduce you to the relevant parts of the used frameworks. Hacking and analysis are encouraged, but only for the scope of this project and on the services you developed yourself. In case the student is interested in .NET, an interoperability analysis between Axis2/Rampart and .NET Azure may be discussed.</p>\r\n<p>The student should present an elaborate comparison, supported by trustworthy reference material, and write this down in a thesis, as well as strategic design decisions and relevant technicalities encountered during the programming of web services for testing purposes and potential changes to the Axis2 XMPP transport.</p>\r\n<p>[1] http://www.soaspecs.com/ws-security.php<br /> [2] Meiko Jensen et al., \"SOA and Web Services: New Technologies, New Standards - New Attacks,\" Proc. Fifth European Conference on Web Services (ECOWS\'07), 2007, pp. 35-44<br /> [3] http://www.saint-andre.com/jabber/Security.pdf</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Computer Aided Design tools voor robotarm sturing','<p>Ontwikkel een teken module, gebruik makend van OpenGL, om de 6DOF (1 lineaire + 5 rotatie vrijheidsgraden) robotarm van het \'Active Perception Lab\' te visualiseren voor een opgegeven set van actuator toestanden.  Ontwikkel vervolgens een botsing detectie module waarmee voor een opgegeven set van actuator toestanden kan nagegaan worden of de robot botst met n van de bijkomend opgegeven voorwerpen uit de omgeving van de robot dan wel met zichzelf.  Gegeven de botsing detectie module, leer met een neuraal netwerk (bvb. Kohonen netwerk) de inverse kinematica transformatie die een opgegeven positie en orintatie van de grijper afbeeldt op de corresponderende set van actuator toestanden (met minimale configuratie verandering tov. de huidige robotarm contiguratie).</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Grafische module voor het VirtualLeaf framework.','<p>VirtualLeaf is een open source modeleer- en simulatietool voor het bestuderen van de groei van plantenbladeren, vertrekkend van een beschrijving van de processen die plaatsvinden op niveau van de individuele cellen van het blad. Daarin spelen celgroei, celdeling en transport van groei regulatoren een rol. In zijn huidige implementatie is de software opgesteld in C++, gebruik makend van de Qt bibliotheek. Hij is draagbaar naar nagenoeg alle platformen (mits beschikbaarheid van Qt).</p>\n\n<p>In het kader van de verdere uitbouw van de simulator dienen twee facetten onderzocht te worden. Het eerste facet bestaat erin de grafische component aan te vullen met een OpenGL module. Hierbij moet mogelijk een refactoring volgens het Model-View-Controller pattern uitgevoerd worden. Het tweede facet bestaat erin na te gaan welke onderdelen van het model geschikt zijn om multi-core architecturen uit te buiten, gebruik makend van OpenMP. De concrete inhoud en stappenplan worden uitgewerkt in overleg met de student.</p>\n\n<p>De activiteiten liggen dus vooral op het gebied van grafisch programmeren, programma design, parallellisatie, steeds in C++ als taal. Het sluit aan bij lopende onderzoeksactiviteit in een samenwerking met onderzoeksgroepen biologie (UA) en computationele biologie (Centrum vor Wiskunde en Informatica, Amsterdam).</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Een individu-gebaseerd model voor de simulatie van de H1N1 pandemie in Belgi','<p>In het Centre for Health Economics Research and Modeling Infectious Diseases (CHERMID) van de de faculteit Geneeskunde (UA) wordt onderzoek verricht rond het modelleren van de verspreiding van infectieziekten in een populatie. </p>\n\n<p>Hiertoe kan men gebruik maken van individu-gebaseerde modellen die in tegenstelling tot zogenaamde mathematische modellen toelaten om de stochasticiteit van een pandemie in rekening te brengen. Deze individu-gebaseerde modellen zijn voor grote populaties echter computationeel zwaar en vereisen efficint programmeerwerk. Tot op heden zijn er slechts vier groepen ter wereld die een soortgelijk model ontwikkeld hebben. En van deze modellen (CSQUID, University of Washington) is zopas publiek beschikbaar gemaakt terwijl de andere modellen in beperkte mate gedocumenteerd werden in de literatuur. </p>\n\n<p>De doelstelling van dit project is om het model van CSQUID te doorgronden, op een efficintere manier aan te passen en gebruiksvriendelijk te maken om het modelleren van de H1N1 pandemie in Belgi mogelijk te maken. CHERMID beschikt over de nodige gegevens om het model toe te passen en realitische simulaties uit te voeren.</p>\n\n<p>Voor meer informatie over het model van CSQUID kan je terecht op http://www.dennischao.com/</p>\n\n<p>Voorkennis:\n De simulator werd ontwikkeld in C++, kennis van deze taal is een must.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Cloud simulator in Java','<p>Een van de hotste topics in hedendaagse IT wereld is Cloud computing, een model waarbij applicaties niet langer lokaal maar wel op servers draaien, en aangestuurd worden over het internet (de cloud). De twee bekendste voorbeelden hiervan zijn Google Apps en Amazon EC2. Terwijl Google diverse applicaties via de webbrowser ter beschikking stelt van gebruikers, laat Amazon toe om in enkele seconden een (bijna) ongelimiteerd aantal servers, in de vorm van virtuele machines, op te starten en te beheren. Daarbij maakt het gebruik van een pay-as-you-go model: je betaalt enkel voor de tijd dat je servers draaien. </p>\n\n<p>Binnen de CoMP groep werd een Discrete Event Simulator ontwikkeld. In discrete-event simulatie wordt de werking van een systeem voorgesteld als een chronologische volgorde van gebeurtenissen. Elke gebeurtenis doet zich voor op een ogenblik in de tijd en markeert een verandering van de toestand in het systeem. Het opzet van deze bachelor thesis is het design en de ontwikkeling van een simulator, die toelaat om cloud computing scenario\'s te simuleren. Zo wordt het mogelijk via simulatie na te gaan hoe cloud providers op een optimale manier de virtuele machines op hun datacenter kunnen schedulen, of welke prijs-mechanismen het voordeligst zijn voor gebruiker of provider.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Meta-data based file archiving','<p>Een van de opvallende recente trends is het opslaan van bestanden in de \"cloud\". Daarbij kunnen bestanden eenvoudig opgeslagen en gedeeld worden over verschillende computers en gebruikers. De synchronisatie van de bestanden loopt geheel via internet. Het bekendste voorbeeld is Dropbox: een online opslagdienst die het mogelijk maakt om volledig via internet bestanden op te slaan en te synchroniseren tussen computers.</p>\n\n<p>Een andere trend is het gebruik van \"tags\". Een tag is een (relevant) sleutelwoord of term geassocieerd met, toegewezen aan of opgenomen in een digitaal bestand (zoals afbeeldingen, video, audio). De tag  geeft aanvullende informatie over het bestand waaraan het is gekoppeld en maakt zodoende sleutelwoordgebaseerde classificatie en indexering mogelijk. Tags worden veel gebruikt in web 2.0 webapplicaties.</p>\n\n<p>Doel van dit eindwerk is het combineren van deze twee trends om te komen tot een meta-data gebaseerd file archiving tool. Concreet moet je een serverapplicatie ontwikkelen die het mogelijk maakt om bestanden te archiveren, verschillende versies ervan bij te houden en ze te organiseren op basis van tags. Zo kan een bestand de tags \"vergadering\", \"2010\", \"bachelor thesis\" en \"student X\" toebedeeld krijgen, en moet het op een eenvoudige manier mogelijk zijn om te zoeken in bestanden op tag, tijdsperiode of filename. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Instant Messenger Plugin for Cloud Logging','<h3>Context</h3>\n\n<p>Steeds meer gegevens worden automatisch bijgehouden en beheerd d.m.v. verschillende cloud diensten (Flickr, Dropbox, Google Mail, Calender, Docs). En van de grote voordelen van deze diensten is het gemak waarmee meerdere toestellen gebruikt kunnen worden om dezelfde data te beheren en bewerken. Nu steeds meer mensen verschillende toestellen (desktop, laptop, gsm, .. ) door mekaar gebruiken wordt de noodzaak van dergelijke diensten enkel groter. Er zijn echter nog steeds gegevens die moeilijk of niet te gesynchronizeerd kunnen worden. Met dit bachelor eindwerk willen we n daarvan wegwerken, de chatlogs in de open source messaging client Pidgin. </p>\n\n<h3>Doel</h3>\n\n<p>Het doel van dit project is het schrijven van een plugin voor Pidgin. De plugin moet er voor zorgen dat all lokale chat logs automatisch synchronizeren met Google Docs. \n* Nieuwe gesprekken moeten op een leesbare en overzichtelijke manier geupload worden naar een spreadsheet. \n* Oude logs die niet lokaal beschikbaar zijn moeten uiteraard ook weer gedownload worden.</p>\n\n<p>In een tweede fase kan er gewerkt worden aan het bruikbaarder maken van deze data. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Reengineering van de ESP website','<p>De ESP website is een handig hulpmiddel voor studenten om geschikte eindwerken/stages uit te kiezen (zoals je nu waarschijnlijk ondervindt..). Er zijn echter een aantal zaken die verbeterd kunnen worden: Het voornaamste probleem is dat de website momenteel vrij onstabiel is. De website is geschreven met behulp van het Ruby On Rails (RoR) framework. Hoewel RoR een veelbelovend platform is om websites in te ontwikkelen, is het tevens een relatief jong platform dat snel evolueert. Als gevolg hiervan is het al meermaals gebeurd dat de ESP website opeens niet meer werkt wanneer de RoR-installatie wordt gepdate.</p>\n\n<p>Het doel van dit project is om op zoek te gaan naar de oorzaak van dit stabiliteitsprobleem en dit trachten op te lossen. Dit kan enerzijds door het onstabiele gedeelte in de code te vervangen door een meer stabiele versie. Anderzijds kan de volledige website ook overgezet worden naar een meer stabiel platform (naar keuze), zoals PHP of JSP. Hiernaast staat de student ook vrij om nieuwe features aan ESP toe te voegen (bv. een Engelstalige versie van de site voor Erasmusstudenten, de mogelijkheid voor elke gebruiker om een persoonlijk lijstje te maken met de projecten die hem/haar interesseren, ...).</p>\n\n<p>Dit project is interessant omdat:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Je werk zal uiteraard geapprecieerd worden door de mensen die ESP onderhouden, maar indirect ook door de gebruikers van de website.</li>\n<li>Je leert werken de nieuwste webtechnologien.</li>\n<li>Je doet ervaring op in het reengineeren (en gedeeltelijk ook reverse engineeren) van een bestaand systeem.</li>\n</ul>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Smartphone Webservice plugin voor Eclipse','<p>Het hedendaagse buzzword cloud computing is bijna niet meer weg te denken.  De inhoud is echter zo breed dat het moeilijk te omschrijven valt. In essentie zou er kunnen gezegd worden dat iets in de cloud gebeurt wanneer het remote op een machine dat via het internet toegankelijk is uitgevoerd wordt.  Dit kan toegepast worden op standaard computers maar ook op de hedendaagse smartphones. Concreet zouden we dus computationele vereisten van programmas op onze smartphone kunnen inwilligen door deze op een remote machine in de cloud uit te voeren. Het gebruik van webservices is een mogelijke techniek om dit te realiseren.</p>\n\n<p>In deze bachelor thesis is het de bedoeling dat er een plugin voor Eclipse ontwikkeld wordt. De plugin moet het eenvoudig mogelijk maken om Java code om te zetten naar een webservice die via een automatisch gegenereerde client vanop een Android platform op basis van SOAP te gebruiken is. Concreet komt het er op neer dat de Axis 2 toolset zo wordt uitgebreid dat de bestaande technologie ook toepasbaar wordt voor Android based smartphones.</p>\n\n<p>Meer informatie is terug te vinden in:</p>\n\n<p>http://developer.android.com/index.html<br />\nhttp://ws.apache.org/axis2/<br />\nhttp://www.w3.org/TR/soap/</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Fast Rendering of Duplo Style Computer Graphics','<p>De bedoeling van dit eindwerk bestaat erin om Duplo blokken op een realistische  en snelle manier te renderen in 3D. Er moet ook een eenvoudige manier/interface voorzien worden om snel constructies bestaande uit vele blokken te bouwen. Verder is het belangrijk het vereiste aantal driehoeken, nodig om elk van de Duplo blokken weer te geven, reeds te reduceren/minimaliseren voordat het Z-buffer algoritme wordt aangeroepen. Optioneel kunnen er blokken met meer complexe vormen en maten voorzien worden, bewegende beelden ondersteund worden, etc. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Designing a Hybrid Cloud for Scientific Computing ','<p>Het outsourcen van IT infrastructuur en zijn beheer heeft recent een extra boost gekregen door de producten die \"cloud\" providers zoals Amazon en Google recent op de markt hebben gebracht. Hierbij wordt klanten de mogelijkheid geboden om via een betaling per gebruikte eenheid resource, en zonder voorafgaandelijke minimum investeringen, gebruik te maken van IT infrastructuur (rekenkracht, opslagruimte, ...), in hun datacenters. Zulk een gebruik is de laatste jaren mogelijk geworden zonder hoge overhead aan configuratie van systemen en applicatie door gebruik te maken van virtualizatie technologie (Xen, VMWare, Microsoft).</p>\n\n<p>Door de schaalvoordelen die cloud providers zoals Amazon en Google kunnen realizeren in de aankoop en beheer van hun infrastructuur, kunnen zij aan competitieve prijzen toegang tot IT infrastructuur aanbieden. Bovendien zorgt hun gebruiksmodel voor een mate van flexibiliteit die een intern data center onmogelijk kan bieden.</p>\n\n<p>Voor vele partijen is het outsourcing verhaal echter geen zwart/wit verhaal. Zo wil men ook de interne infrastructuur zo efficient mogelijk blijven gebruiken, en on-demand beroep doen op diensten van derde partijen wanneer een piek in de belasting van de infrastructuur daarom vraagt. Verder zijn er aspecten rond beveiliging en confidentialiteit van data waarmee rekening moet gehouden worden indien gebruik wordt gemaakt van (een) cloud provider(s).</p>\n\n<p>De actuele vraag bestaat dan ook om de interne infrastructuur op een transparante maar beveiligde wijze uit te breiden met infrastructuur van derde partijen, om zo een \"hybrid\" cloud te bekomen. De term hybrid verwijst naar de combinatie van een interne infrastructuur (private cloud) en een externe infrastructuur (public cloud).</p>\n\n<p>In deze stage willen we dit probleem specifiek belichten vanuit het uitbreiden van de CalcUA rekeninfrastructuur met resources uit EC2. Zowel de integratie van EC2 VMs als workers in de CalcUA Torque queue, alsook het realizeren van een transparante en efficiente koppeling van de CalcUA opslagcapaciteit met deze EC2 VMs moet onderzocht worden.</p>\n\n<p>Het einddoel is dat een UA onderzoeker in tijden van congestie op CalcUA zijn workloads kan uitvoeren op EC2 met een eenvoudige queue keuze. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Instrumentation of Xen VMs for efficient VM scheduling and capacity planning in hybrid clouds','<p>The cost and CO2 emission savings realized by server consolidation through virtualization technology are two of the key drivers for the renewed uptake of this technology. Virtualization in itself however, does not guarantee an efficient consolidation and multiplexing of multiple virtual machine workloads on a single physical server. </p>\n\n<p>An efficient placement of virtual machines requires insight in their system-level performance metrics such as CPU utilization, I/O frequency and intensity, cache hits and misses, VMM context switches and so on, coupled with the intelligent use of this data in scheduling decisions.</p>\n\n<p>The goal of this research internship is to develop code that extracts this information from (multiple) running guest OSes and presents this data in a aggregated, easy to consume fashion. Thereby also minimizing the additional overhead created by such instrumentation and requiring no (or minimal) changes to DomU, or SSH-based access to DomU. </p>\n\n<p>In a second phase, the set of extracted data will be further extended to include metrics that are valuable for the mapping of a VM to virtual machine profiles hosted by cloud providers, and capacity planning in hybrid clouds.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Computer graphics: irregular Z-buffering','<p>A traditional Z-buffering solution for rendering 3D images can easily be extended to incorporate shadow mapping. More specifically, given that we have L light sources, the Z-buffer algorithm has to be run L+1 times, once from the original camera position and once for each light source. Afterward these L+1 results are combined in a pixel-by-pixel computation to support shadow mapping. However, this simple procedure often results in unwanted effects, known as aliasing. </p>\n\n<p>The irregular Z-buffer resolves this problem and is related to the classical Z-buffer  in that it maintains a depth value for each image sample and uses these to determine which geometric elements of a scene are visible. The key difference, however, between the classical Z-buffer and the irregular Z-buffer is that the latter allows arbitrary placement of image samples in the image plane, whereas the former requires samples to be arranged in a regular grid.</p>\n\n<p>These depth samples are explicitly stored in a two-dimensional spatial data structure. During rasterization, triangles are projected onto the image plane as usual, and the data structure is queried to determine which samples overlap each projected triangle. Finally, for each overlapping sample, the standard Z-compare and (conditional) frame buffer update are performed.</p>\n\n<p>The aim of this thesis is to implement and compare different spacial data structures that can be used to implement an irregular Z-buffer in terms of their complexity and run time. A comparison with the traditional Z-buffer to assess the performance penalty is also required.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'VM image distribution and migration in Desktop Clouds','<p>Since the conception of the SETI@home project, voluntueer computing projects have enjoyed a continuous growth over the years. The general-purpose BOINC desktop computing grid now averages about 5.1 petaflops, the more application specific Folding@home sustains over 6.2 petaflops.</p>\n\n<p>Currently there is a great opportunity for introducing virtualization technology into such a large-scale distributed system, in order to form a \"desktop cloud\". Important challenges in this regard are the distribution of virtual machine images to desktop nodes across wide area networks and dealing with the higher volatility in the availability of desktops in such a distributed system. In this regard, VM snapshotting and migration techniques can be employed to transfer the computation to another machine in the network. </p>\n\n<p>This bachelor thesis will develop software and algorithms that address both of these challenges for a desktop cloud system that is based on VirtualBox. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Brute-force Model space exploration for linear regression and variable selection on GPUs ','<p>This project is targeted at exploration of models approximating a given (large) multivariate data set in a least squares sense. The computational power of the GPUs allows data-parallel solution of multiple least-square regression problems at the same time, and calls for an implementation of an intelligent strategy of exploring the space of low-order polynomial models on sub-sets of data variables. </p>\n\n<p>In more detail the challenges of the project consist in the following:</p>\n\n<p>1) Find/write/optimize the GPU-based implementation of a QR algorithm needed for solving least-squares regression problem.</p>\n\n<p>2) Investigate the possibilities of exploring the space of <em>low-order</em> least squares models on <em>all</em> subsets of a given set of data variables, e.g. build a linear model on each variable from the given d variables, all linear (and low-order?) models on two variables, three, etc. The target is to extract a list of best-fit models on different variables, and a variable importance information. </p>\n\n<p>3) Explore the possibilities of intelligent problem formulation such that the GPUs solve the least square problem not only in the data parallel but also in the model-parallel way. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Exploring the state-of-the-art in distributed transaction programming (SOA)','<p>Over the years, industry has developed many proprietary solutions for supporting ACID-type transactions in distributed software systems. In 2005, the OASIS committee proposed the WS-Transaction framework (WS-TX), a set of specifications on top of XML-based web services to support both ACID (backward recovery) and business (forward recovery) transactions.</p>\r\n<p>An in-depth comparison of some prevalent solutions for distributed programming, in particular APIs such as J2EE (JTA) and .NET, will allow you to study how these proprietary solutions are used to support WS-Transaction and hence ensure interoperability between different software technologies.</p>\r\n<p>By investigating and developing a prototype leveraging WS-TX, you will gain experience in open-source platforms such as Apache Kandula2 and the Java METRO stack (i.e. JAX-WS, JAX-B etc) and assess their true interoperability. The student may suggest alternative technologies (e.g. Azure/.NET), and, after careful consideration, a prototype in the context of fault-tolerant recovery blocks can be developed for redundantly deployed web services.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Adaptive User Interfaces','<p>In this project the student shall design a prototypical system to systematically represent, collect, and analyze the actions resulting from expected as well as unexpected human-computer conversations as produced by a graphical user interface. Such system shall instrument Tcl/Tk user interfaces so as to produce a log of those conversations. This log shall then be parsed into a compact code that will then be fed into an analyzer. The latter shall be used to assess dynamically the quality of the interaction experienced by the current user. An illustrative analyzer was developed and will be reused and extended, capable to detect three simple cases of quality of experience failures. The resulting knowledge is reflected to an application layer where a reaction will be planned and executed so as to produce an adapted version of the user interface.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Model checking aspect-oriented programs','<p>Aspect-oriented programming is a programming paradigm that has gained much attention over the last decade; it aims to achieve improved separation of concerns by allowing for the modularization of so-called \"crosscutting concerns\". These concerns are difficult to decompose because they are tangled with other concerns and are often scattered across different places in a program.</p>\r\n<p>Aspect-oriented languages such as AspectJ extend an object-oriented language with aspects, which can be used to contain these crosscutting concerns in seperate modules. While aspects are quite powerful, they also come with their own set of challenges: Aspects can interfere; there can be conflicts and dependencies between aspects; aspects can cause infinite recursions; ...</p>\r\n<p>To tackle these challenges, verification techniques are needed. In particular, this thesis will focus on providing model checking support for the AspectJ language. The core of this model checker has already been provided in the form of delMDSOC, an executable model with support for modularized crosscutting concerns. (<a href=\"http://fots.ua.ac.be/delmdsoc\">http://fots.ua.ac.be/delmdsoc</a>)</p>\r\n<p>The goal of this thesis is to build one (or more) of the following components needed to complete the AspectJ model checker:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A transformation of AspectJ programs towards a corresponding delMDSOC model is needed. (You can think of delMDSOC playing a similar role as the Promela models of the SPIN model checker. Whereas Java programs are often translated to Promela to perform model checking, the goal here is to translate AspectJ programs towards delMDSOC.)</li>\r\n<li>If the property being model-checked is violated, the counterexample that was found and its execution trace need to be presented to the developer in a meaningful way. That is, the developer shouldn\'t be confronted with the underlying delMDSOC model.</li>\r\n<li>Similarly, the developer should not be confronted with delMDSOC when specifying the property he/she wishes to check. Specifying properties should be as easy as possible, assuming that the developer only knows about AspectJ.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This thesis is for you if:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>you\'ve heard of/had a taste of aspect-oriented programming and would like to know more</li>\r\n<li>you like to tinker with cutting edge technology</li>\r\n<li>the idea of making verification techniques more accessible appeals to you</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Notes:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>This project may also be used for Onderzoeksstage I.</li>\r\n<li>A similar thesis for the role-oriented Object Teams language is available at: <a href=\"https://www.esp.win.ua.ac.be/projects/show/622\">https://www.esp.win.ua.ac.be/projects/show/622</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Model checking role-oriented programs','<p>The aim of role-oriented programming is to provide a form of programming that is analogous to our conceptual understanding of the world: To solve complex problems in the real world, people often need to cooperate in teams, where each person has to play one or more particular roles. Role-oriented programming languages, such as <a href=\"http://www.objectteams.org/\">Object Teams</a>, provide similar concepts: Team classes are containers of role classes. Each of these role classes can alter the behaviour of existing (regular) classes. When a team is activated, the roles contained within are applied, meaning that the classes affected by one of these roles are now effectively playing that role.</p>\r\n<p>While these new language constructs are quite powerful, they also come with their own set of challenges, as it is possible to create complex interactions between different teams and roles, as well as interactions between teams and the base program.</p>\r\n<p>To tackle these challenges, verification techniques are needed. In particular, this thesis will focus on providing model checking support for the Object Teams language. The core of this model checker has already been provided in the form of <a href=\"http://fots.ua.ac.be/delmdsoc\">delMDSOC</a>, an executable model with support for modularized crosscutting concerns.</p>\r\n<p>The goal of this thesis is to build one of the following components to complete the Object Teams model checker:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A transformation of Object Teams programs towards a corresponding delMDSOC model is needed. (You can think of delMDSOC playing a similar role as the Promela models of the SPIN model checker. Whereas Java programs are often translated to Promela to perform model checking, the goal here is to translate Object Teams programs towards delMDSOC.)</li>\r\n<li>If the property being model-checked is violated, the counterexample that was found and its execution trace need to be presented to the developer in a meaningful way. That is, the developer shouldn\'t be confronted with the underlying delMDSOC model.</li>\r\n<li>Similarly, the developer should not be confronted with delMDSOC when specifying the property he/she wishes to check. Learning how to specify properties should be as easy as possible, assuming that the developer only knows about Object Teams.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This thesis/internship is for you if:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>you\'re curious about all the different kinds of programming languages out there besides plain vanilla OOP.</li>\r\n<li>you like to tinker with cutting edge technology.</li>\r\n<li>the idea of making verification techniques more accessible appeals to you.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Estimating quality of experience in Human-Computer Interactions','<p>When you use commercially available user interfaces, e.g. those typical of a smartphone,conversations take place between the user side and the computer side: at the one end, e.g. keys are being pressed, screen portions are being touched, words are spoken etc  at the other end, screens are being lled in with widgets, images and textboxes, sounds are emitted, etc. We focus here on the user-to-computer flow of actions, and observe that a large portion of these actions is simply ignored by computers. Some UI, like for Google search, are anticipative, thus they try to predict what the user is expecting (in this case, what he\'s looking for), but the general approach with UI\'s is simply to ignore whatever user action is not associated with a <i>function</i> of the underlying system. By doing so the computer deliberately chooses not to take into account most of the user context. This means we don\'t know how comfortable the computer experience is, how adequate the UI is to the current user, how fluent the person in command is in the conversation with the computer system he\'s using.<p></p>\n\n<p>We propose to set up <b>conversation grammars</b> that encode as many as possible of the key basic actions that the user may take while using a GUI. We then propose to create a time-stamped log of all these actions and parse the \"sentences\" of the human-computer conversations. This is to produce a compact code that could be analysed for misuses, misbehaviors, safety procedure failures etc. The next step would then be to create <b>callbacks</b> to let a system react automatically to the detected Quality-of-Experience failures.<p></p>\n\n<p>The following pictures describe the idea in more detail:\n<ul>\n<li> Here:</p>\n\n<p><center><img src=\"http://www.win.ua.ac.be/~vincenz/wish.png\"></center></p>\n\n<p>you see on the left hand side an illustrative simple UI written with Tcl/Tk. Some conversation has taken place and the right end picture shows a representation in a time / action diagram: Green points are the user events, e.g. circa at time 1400ms the user clicked the Push me button. Events are reported each time the user enters data (e.g. presses a key) or clicks either of the available buttons or slides horizontally or vertically. The more events you catch the more information is acquired (and the more background processing is required of course).\n<li>\nAfter this, an \"iCode\" representing the conversation is sent to a parser;\nthe parser would check that the conversation is \"syntactically OK\" and pack the iCode in a form suitable for analyses. Such analyses may take place at the end of each action or at the end of a given sequence of actions.</p>\n\n<p><li> Actions may take timing aspects into account or neglect them; an example of the former case is given in the following picture:</p>\n\n<p><center><img src=\"http://www.win.ua.ac.be/~vincenz/interaction04.png\"></center></p>\n\n<p>In this case we measure the time gradient while typing in the input field. A typing rate of more than three characters per second is assumed to be senseless and associated with some source of distress. Two cases where timing is not considered are in this picture:</p>\n\n<p><center><img src=\"http://www.win.ua.ac.be/~vincenz/interaction03.png\"></center></p>\n\n<p>Here the system checks whether the \"Push Me\" button has been pressed before any input entry has occurred and whether multiple consecutive occurrences of the same action (\"Push Me\") were observed.</p>\n\n<p><li> Whatever is thus detected, it may be reflected in the application layer of a traditional programming language such as C via a library of callbacks. This will allow adaptations to be triggered whenever specific combinations of QoE failures and other events take place.</p>\n\n<p><li> Adaptation should then be carried out on the Tcl/Tk GUI so as to personalize it with respect to the QoE failures detected. These adaptations may be based e.g. on Abstract Syntax Tree transformations by using a language such as <b>L</b>.\n</ul></p>\n\n<p>This project is built as two separate components: QoE estimation and GUI adaptation. Each component could be carried out by a student.<p><p></p>\n\n<p><a2>Prerequisites</a2>\nInterest in software evolution, adaptive software systems, human-computer interaction. Good programming skills. Experience with Tcl/Tk. Willingness to disseminate the results of this project work in the form of a research paper.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Java integratie in Groove','<p><a href=\"http://groove.cs.utwente.nl/groove-home\">Groove</a> is een tool ontwikkeld aan de universiteit van Twente waarmee transformaties tussen graph-structuren gedefinieerd en uitgevoerd kunnen worden. Het gebied van graph transformaties heeft ontzettend veel toepassingen, gezien veel problemen op een vrij intu&iuml;tieve en visuele manier kunnen uitgedrukt worden als een transformatie tussen twee graphs/modellen. Zo wordt het bijvoorbeeld gebruikt om het gedrag van visuele en tekstuele talen in uit te drukken, om refactorings in (programmeer)talen te specifi&euml;ren, om allerlei modellen te kunnen analyseren, om een model naar een ander abstractieniveau om te zetten, om modellen samen te voegen, te splitsen, enzovoort.</p>\r\n<p>Relatief gezien worden graph transformaties nog vrij weinig gebruikt tegenover de klassieke programmeertalen als Java of C++. Gezien er reeds een rijk aanbod is aan bibliotheken en frameworks in deze talen, komt het zeker van pas om toegang tot zulke talen te hebben vanuit je graph transformaties.</p>\r\n<p>Zulke integratie met programmeertalen ontbreekt momenteel in Groove. Gezien de Groove tool zelf in Java is ge&iuml;mplementeerd, is Java ook de meest geschikte kandidaat om te integreren. Het doel van dit project bestaat er dus uit om het gebruik van Java in Groove\'s graph transformaties mogelijk te maken, bij voorkeur op een manier die zo eenvoudig en intu&iuml;tief mogelijk is naar de Groove gebruiker toe.</p>\r\n<p>Dit project is interessant omdat:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Je kan je software engineering skills loslaten op een bestaand open-source project. Hier komt een deel reverse engineering en mogelijk een gedeelte refactoring bij te pas.</li>\r\n<li>Je leert kennismaken met de wondere wereld van graph transformaties.</li>\r\n<li>Je levert een nuttige bijdrage aan de Groove community.</li>\r\n</ul>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Radio resource management in heterogeneous LTE networks','<p>Recently, the concept of heterogeneous LTE (the next generation of cellular networks, successor to GSM and UMTS) networks has attracted attention. In contrast to homogeneous networks where coverage is only provided by macro base stations (residing on masts of buildings and covering a wide area), in heterogeneous networks also low power pico or femto base stations (residing inside a house or office building, covering smaller areas) will be present. The motivation behind heterogeneous networks is to improve the coverage and capacity at the cell edges, indoor and in hot spots.</p>\r\n<p>This thesis consists of two parts: First an overview of the state-of-the art of radio resource management (RRM) mechanisms (handover, admission control, scheduling, load balancing, ...) for heterogeneous networks should be made, based on articles found in literature and on recent 3GPP standardisation documents. Next, a few of the RRM algorithms should be implemented into an existing simulator (written in OPNET Modeler) that up till now only considers homogeneous networks.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'The power of two paths in grid computing networks','<p>Consider a ring structured grid computing network consisting of n nodes each equipped with K servers (i.e., CPUs). Whenever a task is generated at a node, it will occupy one of the servers. However, if all the servers are occupied, the task is forwarded to the next node. A task may be forwarded as many as n-1 times until a node is found with an available server (if not, the task is dropped). </p>\n\n<p>In this thesis we wish to investigate the possible performance gain by forwarding a task to both the left and right neighbor (whenever all the servers are busy in a node) and to execute the task at the node with the least number of busy servers.  </p>\n\n<p>Apart from a ring structured network, the thesis also aims at exploring other network structures.</p>\n\n<p>The performance evaluation will be done by simulation, hence the thesis does not involve a lot of mathematics.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Multi-server queues with Markovian arrivals and general customer impatience','<p>A traditional M/M/c queueing system has the following properties:</p>\n\n<p>(1) arrivals form a Poisson process with rate lambda\n(2) service times are i.i.d. and follow an exponential distribution\n(3) there are c servers and an infinite waiting room</p>\n\n<p>If we also state that customers are impatient, meaning they leave the system if their waiting time exceeds their patience, we have an M/M/c+GI queue. The amount of patience of a customer follows a general distribution.</p>\n\n<p>Finally if we allow a more general arrival process (a so-called Markovian arrival process) that is also able to capture correlated arrivals, we end up with the MAP/M/c+GI queue.</p>\n\n<p>Within this thesis, we wish to develop an algorithm that is able to compute the waiting time distribution and the probability of abandonment in a MAP/M/c+GI queue using matrix analytic methods.</p>\n\n<p>This thesis is a research oriented thesis that requires a lot of mathematics. If successfully executed, the thesis is likely to result in a publication.  </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Virtual Autonomic Robotic Systems and Environments','<p><strong>Context</strong><br /> Autonomic robots are robots that are able to <em>monitor</em> their environment, <em>analyze</em> the current scenarios they are deployed into, <em>plan</em> strategies able to optimize their mission, and <em>execute</em>such strategies possibly reshaping their software architectures. Within the PATS group we applied this concept last two years respectively (1) on a real-life robot (a Lego MindStorm) and (2) on a virtual environment (microsoft robotics studio). The stronger control on the virtual environment allows us to define complex scenarios and to enact adaptation strategies in a cost-effective way. Furthermore, an OSGi framework (ACCADA) integrated in both the physical and the virtual platform allows us to accomplish in a straightforward way complex adaptations of the software architecture.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Goals</strong><br />This thesis \"template\" may take different research directions, each corresponding to a different master thesis project:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Using a single robot, we would like to further explore adaptation scenarios in the physical, virtual and hybrid environments (the latter combining the first two ones). Aim is to explore how we could design complex scenarios (including e.g. changes in energy availability and failures of system components) and how the system would react to such scenarios. The goals here are to prove that context-awareness and software adaptability allow to make the best of the available resources and conditions and to set up robotic case studies for the ACCADA framework.</li>\r\n<li>A new framework -- called Transformer -- now extends ACCADA and allows to \"merge\" different adaptation concerns on the fly. Embedding Transformer in our robotic \"lab\" is another key research direction to us. A strong prerequisite here is knowledge of OSGi and its Declarative Services.</li>\r\n<li>Experimenting new adaptation \"engines\" and comparing them with in-house solutions ACCADA and Transformer is also one of our research directions. In particular we would like to experiment and assess how Aspect Orientation might be used to adjust autonomically the redundancy requirements of a robotic application. This would encompass e.g. simulating a source of electro-magnetic interference in the virtual environment; designing strategies to cope with such interference; and analyzing how this \"change\" triggers \"adjustments\" throughout the software architecture -- adjustments that allow the system to shield itself optimally against the current threat.</li>\r\n<li>The availability of a virtual environment allows us to model multiple robot instances, thus we would like to begin exploring research paths where multiple \"agents\" collaborate to a common goal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Whatever the topic, a sub-goal shall be to write a research paper (in English) describing your achievements. Further information is available on request.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.microsoft.com/robotics/\">Microsoft Robotics Developer Studio</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://mindstorms.lego.com/en-us/\"> Lego Mindstorms NXT</a></p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Generatie van Cascading Style Sheets uit afbeeldingen');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Web technologies as enablers for SOA front-ends (e.g. AJAX)','<p>Over the years, large enterprises have accumulated a diversity of heterogeneous software systems. However, this heterogeneity imposes limitations on composing and orchestrating such existing legacy IT assets (such as databases, technology-specific software systems, mainframe applications) into more complex services. In the beginning of this decade, this issue led to the concept of service-oriented architectures (SOA) in which IT is flexibly structured by splitting up the business logic in a number of software components that are exposed as services with explicit, platform-neutral interfaces. Actually this service-oriented computing paradigm comprises the best practices in distributed computing of &ndash; roughly estimated &ndash; the past twenty years, and commercially backed by major industry concerns, SOA continues to gain in popularity. As one possible SOA implementation technology, XML-based web services have managed to become the de facto standard for distributed enterprise applications.</p>\r\n<p>The emphasis of end-user applications has gradually shifted from the user&rsquo;s local PC to remotely hosted web applications. Over the years, portal systems have caught particular attention because of their agility and potential for the development of <strong>integrated applications</strong>. In fact, recently developed portal technologies offer support to combine portlets, each representing a single application user interface, such that the end user is presented one unified presentation of the required information. This approach can deliver highly personalized application interfaces, considering user role, profile, personal and/or device settings.</p>\r\n<p>The aim of this thesis is to investigate how existing web presentation technologies such as AJAX can effectively be used to implement application portlets. In other words, given any set of SOA applications (i.e. lower web tier and business tier &ndash; see figure below), which technologies offer ample facilities to support user-service interaction. Obviously, this covers classical request-response (synchronous) interaction, but also asynchronous communication &ndash; notifications.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://download.oracle.com/javaee/5/tutorial/doc/figures/overview-multitieredApplications.gif\" alt=\"Diagram of multitiered application structure, including client tier, web tier, business tier, and EIS tier.\" /></p>\r\n<p>In this thesis, you will gain experience in open-source portal implementation (selection is yours), Java web tiers programming (including portlets) and AJAX. You develop a prototype portal with some portlets for testing applications. The essential part of this thesis is the use of the Web Services Remote Portlets (WSRP) specification [2]. Apart from AJAX which is mandatory, the student can determine which other technologies to assess. The result of the thesis is a thorough comparison in which different technologies are assessed and compared in the context of SOA WSRP-enabled portals.</p>\r\n<p>Notions on SOAP and WSDL and their impact on web services are useful. No actual experience in developing web services is required.</p>\r\n<p>Some references:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/webservices/library/ws-wsajax/\">Call SOAP Web services with Ajax</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Web_Services_for_Remote_Portlets\">WS Remote Portlets (WSRP), Wikipedia intro</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Energy Efficient Data Center Scheduling','<p>A cloud provider\'s large-scale data centers are designed and built to be energy efficient, as their power needs exceed those of previous generations by multiple orders of magnitude. Among other things, data centers are adopting advanced power management hardware, water-based cooling systems, and denser server configurations, making these facilities much different from conventional air-&shy;conditioned server rooms. These data centers can use as much electricity as a small city. Thus, their implantation in areas where cheap electricity is available is crucial. By placing a data center directly at the site of a (renewable) energy source, expensive electrical transmissions costs could already be eliminated.</p>\r\n<p>Electricity prices fluctuate heavily, and allow for optimization: the challenge is figuring out how to build software that can monitor electricity prices or electricity generation in a data center, prioritize compute jobs and then figure out when and where to send those jobs based on whether the wind is blowing, the sun is shining or the available electricity is cheap.</p>\r\n<p>As part of a bachelor thesis, a cloud simulator was developed on top of CoMP\'s Discrete Event Simulation framework. In the cloud simulator, the interactions between customers scheduling applications \"in the cloud\" and providers with a number of data centers offering virtual machines with different characteristics and prices are simulated on a fine grained level.</p>\r\n<p>In this master thesis/internship you:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>investigate whether simple models or data exist for for electricity consumption in servers and cloud data centers.</li>\r\n<li>extend the cloud simulator and incorporate an extensive model for power consumption and fluctuating electricity prices.</li>\r\n<li>try to implement and evaluate a <em>follow-the-sun</em> data center scheduling strategy that that reduces costs by migrating virtual machines to data centers where energy consumption is cheaper.</li>\r\n</ul>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Evaluating Price Setting Policies for Cloud Providers','<p>Amazon\'s Elastic Compute Service (EC2) cloud offering allows consumers to allocate virtual machine instances, that run a user-defined operating system and application software stack, in its data centers in an on-demand fashion. That is, a user has the ability to allocate or deallocate virtual machine instances at any time according to the its workload demand.</p>\r\n<p>In terms of pricing, a user has the option: <br /> 1) To allocate instances on a spot market with prices that vary hourly. Instances can be shut down by EC2 if the consumer\'s bid no longer exceeds the spot market price. <br /> 2) To buy reserved instances with a guaranteed availability. This requires an upfront payment for an instance for a one or three year period, supplemented with usage based pricing based on a fixed price. <br /> 3) To allocate on-demand instances that are priced with a fixed charging rate. Once launched, these instances are guaranteed to be kept live as long as the user pays for them. In principle, a user does not have a full guarantee of being able to launch a (set of) on-demand instance(s).</p>\r\n<p>As part of a bachelor thesis, a cloud simulator was developed on top of CoMP\'s Discrete Event Simulation framework. In the cloud simulator, the interactions between customers scheduling applications \"in the cloud\" and providers with a number of data centers offering virtual machines with different characteristics and prices are simulated on a fine grained level.</p>\r\n<p>In this master thesis/internship you:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>extend the cloud simulator and incorporate on-demand, spot and reserved price setting policies.</li>\r\n<li>evaluate the interaction between these policies with relation to the cloud provider\'s profit and data center utilization level.</li>\r\n<li>evaluate Amazon\'s spot market model and investigate whether adaptations to that model or other spot market models (such as auctions) could result in an improvement in terms of profit, utilization or data center efficiency.</li>\r\n</ul>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Automated Benchmarking of Virtualized Environments','<p>The cost and CO2 emission savings realized by server consolidation through virtualization technology are two of the key drivers for the renewed uptake of this technology. Virtualization in itself however, does not guarantee an efficient consolidation and multiplexing of multiple virtual machine workloads on a single physical server.</p>\r\n<p>An efficient placement of virtual machines requires insight in their system-level performance metrics such as CPU utilization, I/O frequency and intensity, cache hits and misses, VMM context switches and so on, coupled with the intelligent use of this data in scheduling decisions.</p>\r\n<p>Current research has resulted in a benchmarking tool which extracts this information from (multiple) running guest OS\'s and presents this data in an aggregated, easy to consume fashion. The system is stressed by automatically running a varied set of existing benchmarks to get a view of the workload interference under different load types. The goal of this research internship is to help extend and improve the current tool in several ways.</p>\r\n<p>Several possible extensions to the benchmark software and techniques are still open: * Increasing and validating the accuracy of certain metrics * Research into and expansion of the benchmark set * Modification of additional benchmarks to include a throttling function (e.g. rate limit to only use X amount of CPU cycles). * Automating the installation and configuration of the base system (tool + modified Xen deployment) to speed up deployment on different server types</p>\r\n<p>Depending on your personal interest and the priorities within our research group a personalized project can be determined.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Optimistic Parallel and Distributed Discrete Event Simulation');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'A Tracing Framework for Discrete-Event Simulations','<p>Computer simulations have become an indispensable tool for the empirical study of large-scale systems, because the evaluation of new algorithms on real testbeds is impeded by their limited flexibility, controllability and availability. In addition, the costs of building and configuring large-scale testbeds are high. For this reason, researchers turn to simulation to evaluate new algorithms and techniques.</p>\r\n<p>Within the CoMP group, a discrete event simulator was developed for the simulation of communication sequential processes (CSP) and interactions between entities connected in a communication network. A discrete event simulation advances by executing events in chronological order according to their firetime. Each event changes the state of the simulation model and may trigger the creation new events that will be executed at a future point in time.</p>\r\n<p>The development of a general purpose discrete event simulator is a complex process where good scalability properties and simulator performance are critical to succeed. Nevertheless, the real-world performance of a particular simulator or simulation technique is difficult to evaluate and assess, as it often depends heavily on the simulation model properties (e.g. network delays, amount of interactions, entity behavior, etc.). Additionally, a performance comparison between several discrete-event simulators is difficult to accomplish without actually executing a range of models in every simulator.</p>\r\n<p>The goal of this internship is to develop a tracing framework to collect information on the behavior of discrete-event simulations. The traces should support information at different levels of detail, depending on user preference or performance considerations. In its most detailed form, a trace should contain simulation setup details (e.g. network model used) together with detailed event trace data (e.g. event duration) and aggregated statistics (e.g. total runtime) about the whole simulation run or calculated at regular intervals. Based on these traces, individual simulation runs can be replayed and evaluated, even in different simulator implementations (e.g. SimGrid). To control the overhead associated with the collection of these traces (discrete-event simulators can execute hundreds of thousands of events per second), several trace data reduction and aggregation methods need to be investigated and implemented.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Evaluation and implementation of Event Queue ADTs','<p>Computer simulations have become an indispensable tool for the empirical study of large-scale systems, because the evaluation of new algorithms on real testbeds is impeded by their limited flexibility, controllability and availability. In addition, the costs of building and configuring large-scale testbeds are high. For this reason, researchers turn to simulation to evaluate new algorithms and techniques.</p>\n\n<p>Within the CoMP group, a discrete event simulator was developed for the simulation of communication sequential processes (CSP) and interactions between entities connected in a communication network. A discrete event simulation advances by executing events in chronological order according to their firetime. Each event changes the state of the simulation model and may trigger the creation new events that will be executed at a future point in time.</p>\n\n<p>The development of a general purpose discrete event simulator is a complex process where good scalability and performance are critical to succeed. Therefore, each component in a performance critical path in the simulator core should be optimized heavily. </p>\n\n<p>An essential component of a discrete-event simulator core is the queue containing future events or the event queue. This is typically implemented by a priority queue ADT, which orders events by their firetimes. Many priority queue implementations exist and some are more suitable than others in this context (e.g. Ladder Queue).</p>\n\n<p>The goal of this internship is to investigate whether the currently used queue implementation (java.util.PriorityQueue) can be replaced by a version that is more optimized for discrete event simulation. This study should contain a comparison of which priority queue implementations are currently used in other major discrete event simulators (e.g. NS3) and a performance evaluation of different queue implementations in different simulation application scenarios. Additionally, the design and performance of an autotuning algorithm that tweaks the queue implementation during simulation is to be investigated.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Dependable, lightweight and service-oriented applications on smartphones','<p>As smartphones have become increasingly popular, and with data connectivity charges for mobile devices gradually dropping, an increasing amount of data-driven applications have become available. This may include, e.g., mobile banking, equity trading and security-related supervision alerts. Some of these applications may be expected to be reliable, some may target a trade-off with data connectivity costs.</p>\r\n<p>In this thesis, the student can explore the different transport types for web services communication, including, amongst others, HTTP, POP, SMTP, SMS and XMPP. Also, depending on the environment in which the device is located, different network facilities may be available, and it may be beneficial or even mandatory to switch network, thereby targeting either throughput and/or cost effectiveness.</p>\r\n<p>This subject focuses on adaptability of mobile web services, and builds on the Apache MUSE and Axis2 projects. A significant part of the thesis is the conception of a holistic solution to improve availability and adaptability of such reliable web services. This encompasses research to a properly designed solution, and then programming to show a prototype and perform adequate experimentation. Minor hacking in either of the previously listed open-source frameworks may be involved, during which you&rsquo;ll be intensively assisted if you require help.</p>\r\n<p>More information can be obtained at promoter and mentor.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Geautomatiseerde selectie van patinten voor klinische studies','<p>Op het Universitair Ziekenhuis Antwerpen worden jaarlijks meer dan 200 klinische studies uitgevoerd. Voor elke klinische studie worden daarbij een set van inclusie- en exclusiecriteria opgesteld waaraan patinten moeten voldoen om in aanmerking te kunnen komen voor een studie. Omdat men vaak op voorhand wenst te kunnen berekenen wat het aantal mogelijke subjecten is in aanmerking komt voor een specifieke studie, wil men een volledig automatisch systeem ontwerpen dat een shortlist aan patinten oplevert die potentieel in aanmerking komen voor een klinische studie. </p>\n\n<p>Dit project omvat de ontwikkelen van een prototype applicatie voor automatische selectie van patinten. Een aantal grote componenten zijn daarbij belangrijk: 1) je bedenkt een nieuwe algoritme voor het bepalen van een ranking voor de gencludeerde patinten; 2) je ontwikkelt een formele xml beschrijving van de inclusie- en exclusiecriteria waarbij gesteund wordt op internationale standaarden voor codering van medische terminologien (LOINC); 3) je ontwikkelt een aantrekkelijke user interface voor het opvolgen van klinische studies waarbij ook een grafische voorstelling van de selectiecriteria per patint wordt getoond.</p>\n\n<p>Vereiste voorkennis</p>\n\n<p>Programmeerervaring (Python, Java, ), sterke interesse in softwareontwikkeling voor de gezondheidszorg, eigen inbreng en zelfstandigheid zijn cruciaal.</p>\n\n<p>Contact: tim.van.den.bulcke@uza.be</p>\n\n<p>Referenties:</p>\n\n<p> Onderzoeksgroepen: ADReM (www.adrem.ua.ac.be), biomina (www.biomina.be)</p>\n\n<p> Universitair Ziekenhuis Antwerpen: www.uza.be</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Het gebruik van data mining en statistische technieken voor kwaliteitscontrole van medische gegevens','<p>In het Universitair Ziekenhuis Antwerpen worden jaarlijks meer dan 50.000 patinten opgenomen. Aan elk van de patintenverblijven worden n of meerdere codes toegekend die o.a. de diagnosen en ingrepen op een gestructureerde manier vastleggen. Dit gebeurt aan de hand van een internationale standaard, nl. ICD-9-CM. Daarnaast wordt ook een aparte set van codes (RIZIV nomenclatuur) gebruikt voor rapportering van de facturatiegegevens aan de overheid (RIZIV). Beide codes vormen samen met een reeks andere anonieme patintgegevens (leeftijd, geslacht, woonplaats, ) de set van minimale klinische gegevens (MKG) die gerapporteerd worden aan de overheid.</p>\n\n<p>Dit eindwerk heeft tot doel om data mining technieken te gebruiken om een aantal zorgkwaliteitsparameters (zoals bvb. de verblijfsduur, sterfte en ziekenhuiskosten)  voorspellen aan de hand van ICD-9-CM en/of RIZIV codes die toegekend zijn aan een patint. Anderzijds zullen een aantal data mining en statistische technieken gebruikt worden om de kwaliteit van de gegevens zelf te evalueren (outlier detectie, onverklaarbare discrepanties tussen ICD-9-CM en RIZIV codering, ). Het is belangrijk om de bekomen resultaten visueel goed voor te stellen zodat  De resultaten van dit onderzoek zullen zowel ziekenhuis als patinten meer inzicht geven in de parameters die de kwaliteit van hun verblijf kwantificeren en zullen tevens de kwaliteit van de gerapporteerde gegevens zelf verhogen.</p>\n\n<p>Je taken binnen dit eindwerk zullen zich voornamelijk situeren rond data mining, data analyse en ook visualisatie van de bekomen resultaten. Afhankelijk van de eigen interesses en in samenspraak met de promotoren kan gekozen worden voor verschillende data mining technieken. Je krijgt tevens de mogelijkheid om een wetenschappelijke publicatie te schrijven op basis van je onderzoek.</p>\n\n<p>Voorkennis</p>\n\n<p>ambitieus en zelfstandig, ervaring met data mining en/of statistische software (R, Matlab, Weka, SAS, SPSS, ), brede wetenschappelijke interesse (medisch, algoritmisch)</p>\n\n<p>Contact: tim.van.den.bulcke@uza.be</p>\n\n<p>Referenties:</p>\n\n<p> UZA: http://www.uza.be\n ICD9: http://www.cdc.gov/nchs/icd.htm\n MKG: http://www.zorg-en-gezondheid.be/data_mkg.aspx</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Identificatie van risico groepen voor colorectale kanker met behulp van data mining methoden');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Network Security in IPv6 Networks','<p><span id=\"result_box\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\">The</span> <span class=\"hps\">globally available</span> <span class=\"hps\">IPv4</span> <span class=\"hps\">address space</span> <span class=\"hps\">is exhausted</span><span>,</span> <span class=\"hps alt-edited\">in Asia</span> <span class=\"hps\">and Oceania</span><span>, one can</span> <span class=\"hps\">now</span> <span class=\"hps\">only</span> <span class=\"hps\">obtain</span> <span class=\"hps\">IPv6</span> <span class=\"hps\">addresses</span><span>.</span> <span class=\"hps\">Although</span> <span class=\"hps\">IPv6</span> <span class=\"hps\">was</span> <span class=\"hps\">defined</span> <span class=\"hps\">in 1998</span><span>, its use is still limited</span><span>.</span> <span class=\"hps\">In terms of</span> <span class=\"hps\">security</span> <span class=\"hps\">some old</span> <span class=\"hps\">problems remain</span> <span class=\"hps\">to be solved</span> <span class=\"hps\">in this</span> <span class=\"hps\">new</span> <span class=\"hps\">protocol and</span> <span class=\"hps\">some</span> <span class=\"hps\">new features</span> <span class=\"hps\">also introduce</span> <span class=\"hps\">new risks</span><span>.</span> <span class=\"hps\">Besides these</span> <span class=\"hps\">problems</span><span>,</span> <span class=\"hps\">there are also</span> <span class=\"hps\">transition</span> <span class=\"hps\">mechanisms</span> <span class=\"hps\">provided to connect</span> <span class=\"hps\">IPv4</span> <span class=\"hps\">networks</span> <span id=\"result_box\" lang=\"en\">to</span> <span class=\"hps\">an IPv6</span> <span class=\"hps\">backbone</span><span>,</span> </span><span id=\"result_box\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\"><span id=\"result_box\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\">to connect </span></span>IPv6</span> <span class=\"hps\">networks</span> <span class=\"hps\">over an IPv4</span> <span class=\"hps\">backbone or</span> <span class=\"hps\">even</span> <span class=\"hps\">for</span> <span class=\"hps\">IPv4</span> <span class=\"hps\">and IPv6</span> <span class=\"hps\">networks</span> <span class=\"hps\">to communicate</span><span>.</span> <span class=\"hps\">These</span> <span class=\"hps\">mechanisms</span> <span class=\"hps\">are necessary</span> <span class=\"hps\">in the transition</span> <span class=\"hps\">from IPv4</span> <span class=\"hps\">to IPv6</span><span>,</span> <span class=\"hps\">but</span> <span class=\"hps\">bring</span> <span class=\"hps\">in turn</span> <span class=\"hps atn\">a lot of (</span><span>security</span><span>)</span> <span class=\"hps\">problems</span><span>.</span><br /><br /> <span class=\"hps\">It is</span> <span class=\"hps\">the intention</span> <span class=\"hps\">of this thesis</span> <span class=\"hps\">to go deeper into</span> <span class=\"hps\">the</span> <span class=\"hps\">IPv6</span> <span class=\"hps\">protocol with</span> <span class=\"hps\">security in mind</span><span>.</span> <span class=\"hps\">What</span> <span class=\"hps\">are the risks</span> <span class=\"hps\">of the protocol</span><span>?</span> <span class=\"hps\">Solutions</span> <span class=\"hps\">have already been</span> <span class=\"hps\">defined?</span> <span class=\"hps\">What about</span> <span class=\"hps\">the</span> <span class=\"hps\">transition</span> <span class=\"hps\">mechanisms</span><span>?</span><br /><br /> <span class=\"hps\">The thesis</span> <span class=\"hps\">consists of both</span> <span class=\"hps\">a theoretical part</span> <span class=\"hps\">where the</span> <span class=\"hps\">protocols</span> <span class=\"hps atn\">(</span><span>IPv6</span> <span class=\"hps\">and transition</span> <span class=\"hps\">mechanisms</span><span>)</span><span>,</span> <span class=\"hps\">their problems</span> <span class=\"hps\">and</span> <span class=\"hps\">the</span> <span class=\"hps\">solutions will</span> <span class=\"hps\">be</span> <span class=\"hps\">discussed</span> <span class=\"hps\">and</span> <span class=\"hps\">a practical part</span> <span class=\"hps\">where some</span> <span class=\"hps\">problems may also</span> <span class=\"hps\">be demonstrated</span> <span class=\"hps\">using </span><span class=\"hps\">a</span> <span class=\"hps\">limited network</span> <span class=\"hps\">setup</span><span>.</span></span></p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Enhanced IPv6 support in the Click Modular Router','<p>The Click Modular Router platform (http://read.cs.ucla.edu/click/) is a powerful and flexible environment for developing routers. Click is based on the concept that a router can be built up using a number of (small) elements or building blocks that are responsible for processing packets and storing information. Each element has a very specific purpose (e.g. processing ARP request messages) and the different elements that are needed to construct a router are connected by building up a directed graph, using a click script. The Click framework already offers a lot of \"standard\" elements for most packet processing functions.</p>\r\n<p>Now that the IANA IPv4 address pool is depleted, more and more router implementations are built using IPv6 packets. Click provides the most basic elements that offer IPv6 support, but the IPv6 elements are not always as powerful or as fast as their IPv4 counterparts. Moreover, some functionality that is available for IPv4 packets is entirely missing for IPv6 packets, making the construction of IPv6 routers more troublesome. Some elements still contain annoying bugs...</p>\r\n<p>The purpose of this project is twofold: identify the functionality available for IPv4 but missing (or implemented with bugs) for IPv6 in the click elements and to add this missing functionality or fix the bugs, making the IPv4 and IPv6 stacks equally versatile. Secondly, benchmark the IPv4 and IPv6 elements, identifying possible performance bottlenecks in the IPv6 implementation and, if possible, improve the performance of the IPv6 stack.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'TCP support in the Click Modular Router','<p>The Click Modular Router framework (http://read.cs.ucla.edu/click) offers a wide variety of elements that can be used to build packet processors. While Click has built-in support for the UDP protocol, TCP support is lacking in the standard click element tree.</p>\r\n<p>A possible solution to this problem is the use of the \"rump kernel\" (https://wiki.netbsd.org/rumpkernel/). Rump kernels are essentially stripped down versions of the NetBSD kernel that can be run as a normal userspace executable on any Linux system. By combining a stripped-down version of the kernel that includes a fully functional BSD TCP/IP networking stack and the Click router, it should be possible to use TCP functionality in combination with Click.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.02px;\">The goal of this thesis is to build a working Click configuration, combined with a rump kernel setup and demonstrate that TCP can be used as a protocol using Click. Subsequently, a performance analysis is expected that compares this setup with several others, e.g. a native Linux setup.</span></p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Recommender Systems','<p>In this thesis, you are expected to do a thorough literature study of state-of-the-art recommender systems.  A recommender system attempts to recommend information items (movies, TV program/show/episode, video on demand, music,[1] books, news, images, web pages, scientific literature such as research papers etc.) that are likely to be of interest to the user, based on user profiles which are built (mined) from historical data.  The focus of this thesis will be on recommender systems that are based on pattern mining methods as investigated by the data mining team of ADReM. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Social network analysis','<p>In this thesis, you are expected to do a thorough literature study of state-of-the-art social network analysismethods. Social Network Analysis (SNA) is the mapping and measuring of relationships and flows between people, groups, organizations, computers, URLs, and other connected information/knowledge entities. The nodes in the network are the people and groups while the links show relationships or flows between the nodes.  SNA provides both a visual and a mathematical analysis of human relationships. The focus of this thesis will be on SNA techniques that are based on pattern mining methods as investigated by the data mining team of ADReM. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Mining Train Delay Data','<p>During the past five years, the punctuality of the Belgian trains has gradually decreased towards a worrisome level. Meanwhile, the number of passengers, and therefore also the number of trains necessary to transport those passengers has increased. Even though the infrastructure capacity is also slightly increasing by doubling the number of tracks on the main lines around Brussels, the punctuality is still decreasing. \nTo solve the decreasing punctuality problem, its main causes should be discovered, but because of the complexity of the network, it is hard to trace their true origin. It may happen that a structural delay in a particular part of the network seems to be caused by busy traffic, although in reality this might be caused by a traffic operator in a seemingly unrelated place, who makes a bad decision every day, unaware of the consequences of his decision. \nIn this thesis, you will study the application of pattern mining techniques, as developed by the ADReM data mining team,  in order to discover related train delays in this data. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Approximate Instant Pattern Mining','<p>Pattern mining methods are typically very time and space consuming and discover huge amounts of patterns.  An end-user, however, who is only interested in exploring the generated patterns, does not like to wait too long in order to see much more patterns as he will ever be able to investigate.  It would be much more convenient if he would receive approximately correct pattern much faster. In this thesis, you will study approximate query answering techniques and investigate to what extent they can be applied for mining interesting itemsets. </p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Python-like Human-Usable Textual Notation (HUTN)','<p>To represent models, there is always a choice of using a graphical notation (such as the UML)\nor a textual notation (such as Promela). In our meta-modelling tool <a href=\"http://atom3.cs.mcgill.ca/\">AToM^3</a>,\nthe focus has mainly been on modelling and synthesis of syntax directed, graphical modelling environments.\nIn the tool AToMPM, which is currently under development, both textual and graphical syntax must\nbe supported.</p>\n\n<p>The goal of this thesis is to create a Human-usable textual notation (HUTN) that has a Python look-and-feel.\nIt should be possible to specify a textual domain-specific language (DSL) with similar support as its graphical counterpart.\nThis means that from a DSL specification, a modelling environment is automatically generated,\nthat includes parsing of a textual model and representing it in the AToMPM kernel, syntax highlighting,\nauto-correction and auto-completion, etc. <a href=\"http://www.eclipse.org/Xtext/\">Xtext</a>  is a good example of such a tool.</p>\n\n<p>This project allows you to:</p>\n\n<p>- make a significant contribution on a new, state-of the art modelling tool,</p>\n\n<p>- work together closely with MSDL members, as your work will be highly relevant to the research group,</p>\n\n<p>- develop a tool that will actually be used world-wide.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Textual transformation language for AToMPM','<p>In Model-Driven Engineering, models, code or other software artefacts can be generated from formal models by means of model transformation. In our tool <a href=\"http://atom3.cs.mcgill.ca\">AToM<sup>3</sup></a>, graphical models can be transformed using a graphical rule-based transformation system.</p>\r\n<p>The goal of this thesis is to create a textual transformation language for our new tool meta-modelling and model transformation tool AToMPM. The underlying transformation kernel of graph rewriting remains the same as the one in <a href=\"http://atom3.cs.mcgill.ca\">AToM<sup>3</sup></a>. <a href=\"http://www.eclipse.org/atl/\">ATL</a> is an example of a textual transformation language. Throughout this thesis, you will benefit from the work done by former MSDL researcher <a href=\"http://msdl.cs.mcgill.ca/people/eugene/\">Eugene Syriani</a>. In his work, transformation languages can be built modularly from T-Core, a collection of primitive model transformation language building blocks. Your new textual transformation language will be mapped to these building blocks.</p>\r\n<p>This project allows you to:</p>\r\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; make a significant contribution on a new, state-of the art modelling tool,</p>\r\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; work together closely with MSDL members, as your work will be highly relevant to the research group,</p>\r\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; make use of and build on the innovative work done by Eugene Syriani.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Semi-automated migration of modelling artefacts','<p>Software artefacts are subject to change.\nIn domain-specific modelling, not only programs, but even domain-specific modelling languages (DSMLs) are created\nthroughout the development cycle of a system. These languages are subject to change as well.\nHowever, changing a DSML affects related software artefacts, most notably instances of the DSML (models) and model transformations\nfrom or to the DSML. This means that these related artefacts have to be migrated.</p>\n\n<p>The goal of this thesis is to create support for migration in our new tool AToMPM.\nIn AToMPM, changes that are applied to a DSML specification are recorded.\nFrom these recorded \"edit-operations\", a default migration for related artefacts must be suggested.\nMoreover, an environment must be developed to allow customisation of these suggested migrations.\nIn this thesis you will elaborate research done by <a href=\"http://msdl.cs.mcgill.ca/people/bart/\">Bart Meyers</a>.</p>\n\n<p>This project allows you to:</p>\n\n<p>- make a significant contribution on a new, state-of the art modelling tool,</p>\n\n<p>- work together closely with MSDL members, especially Bart Meyers,\n           as your work will be highly relevant to his research and to the research group in general,</p>\n\n<p>- contribute to the research community with innovative work.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Hybrid concrete syntax of modelling languages','<p>In Model-Driven Engineering, models can be represented in different ways.\nTherefore, the same model can have different concrete syntaxes (i.e., the way the model looks).\nIn some cases, the most appropriate way to visualise models is a combination of textual and graphical notations.\nIn other cases, a model is represented in more than one (textual ) concrete syntax.\nIn yet other cases, it is desirable to change the ratio of textual representation versus graphical\nrepresentation, and being able to control this ratio with a \"slider\".</p>\n\n<p>The goal of this thesis is to allow a concrete syntax that is a hybrid of different representations.\nThe above scenarios should be made possible using our new tool AToMPM.\nAs the real-time rendering of concrete syntaxes is already supported, you will implement techniques that allow parser switching,\nrepresentation of multiple small text editors in a graphical editor, implementing a graphical vs. textual slider, etc.\nThis thesis builds from the work done by <a href=\"http://msdl.cs.mcgill.ca/people/jake/\">Jacob Beard</a> on graphical user interfaces.</p>\n\n<p>This project allows you to:</p>\n\n<p>- make a significant contribution on a new, state-of the art modelling tool,</p>\n\n<p>- work together closely with MSDL members, as your work will be highly relevant to the research group,</p>\n\n<p>- contribute to the research community with innovative work.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Rule-based Modelling of Non-Player Character (NPC) Behaviour ','<p>Recently, the complexity of modern, real-time computer games has increased drastically. The need for sophisticated game AI, in particular for Non-Player Characters (NPCs), grows with the demand for realistic games. Writing consistent, re-useable and efficient AI code has become hard. Modelling game AI at an appropriate abstraction level using an appropriate modelling language based on rules has many advantages. </p>\n\n<p>This thesis will explore the modelling, simulation and automatic synthesis of NPC behaviour. Cognitive architectures based on rules such as in <a href=\"http://act-r.psy.cmu.edu/\">ACT-R</a> will be used as a source of inspiration. The focus will be on the automatic synthesis of variants of behaviour models.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Transforming Statecharts to Petri Nets','<p>The Statecharts family of formalisms allows for the description of reactive, timed systems behaviour. It is mostly used for simulation and code synthesis.\nPetri nets allow for the modelling and analysis of properties such as reachability, deadlock, and conservation of possibly non-deterministic systems behaviour. This thesis investigates the automatic transformation of Statecharts models to behaviourally equivalent Petri net models.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Domain-Specific Modelling and Model Transformation to support Collaborative Work on Android','<p>Android is a software stack for mobile devices that includes an operating system, middleware and key applications. The Android SDK provides the tools and APIs to develop applications that run on Android-powered devices such as the HTC Magic smartphone.</p>\n\n<p>Domain-Specific Modelling (DSM) and Model Transformation (MT) have the potential to support rapid development and synthesis of new applications on Android.</p>\n\n<p>This thesis investigates the power and limitations of DSM and MT. The focus of this work is on the support of collaborative work on the Android Platform.\nThe <a href=\"http://astreo.ii.uam.es/~jlara/metaDepth/\">metaDepth</a> meta-modelling framework and tool will be used. This work will be carried out in collaboration with Prof. <a href=\"http://arantxa.ii.uam.es/~jlara/\">Juan de Lara</a>, the author of metaDepth.</p>\n');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'The future of data downloads: sparse signal processing','<p>The explosion of mobile devices, e.g., smartphones, tablets, is clearly visible. It has been projected that there will be 10 billion such devices in the next ten years. The evermore sophisticated mobile devices demand not only more powerful hardware, such as processors, memory, larger screens, but also monster-size wireless data downloads. However, while efforts have been made to free up more spectrum, the wireless bandwidth is not infinitely extendable.</p>\r\n<p>Interviewed at the 2011 Mobile World Congress, Qualcomm\'s CEO alarmed that \"the issue is that the spectrum is not infinite. It\'s not like I can put another fiber to your phone and you carry it around behind you. There is always so much spectrum. The systems work at a certain rate, you can get so much data downloads and the operator has to deal with that fact.\"</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://edition.cnn.com/video/#/video/business/2011/02/17/qmb.boulden.jacobs.cnn\">Paying for mobile downloads</a> (CNN: February 17, 2011)</p>\r\n<p>Current debates on fee charges over wireless data transmission is connected to an attempt to provide application developers incentives to be more efficient in delivering content. On top of that, if we are able to recover the same signals/images from fewer measurements (or samplings), then we may also reduce the amount of data being transmitted.</p>\r\n<p>Recently, our research group has made some breakthroughs in sparse interpolation and approximation: if a signal has a certain compact representation, then we can exploit the sparsity and reconstruct such a signal from a reduced number of samplings. So far our results have enabled us to contribute to projects aiming at the efficiency in processing health monitoring signals (for example, see www.smartcare.be).</p>\r\n<p>As a new approach toward signal processing, the potential of sparse sampling is far from being fully realized. As we have further identified several interesting issues in the implementation, this project offers the opportunity to participate in this promising research field and acquire knowledge in applying mathematical and/or computational results to engineering applications.</p>');
insert into document (documentID, lang, content) values (default, engels, 'Hyperspectral modelling','<p>Hyperspectral imaging collects and processes information from across the electromagnetic spectrum. Unlike the human eye, which just sees visible light, hyperspectral imaging is more like the eyes of the mantis shrimp, which can see visible light as well as from the ultraviolet to infrared.</p>\r\n<p>Humans build sensors and processing systems to provide the same type of capability for application in agriculture, mineralogy, physics, and surveillance. Hyperspectral sensors look at objects using a vast portion of the electromagnetic spectrum. Certain objects leave unique \'fingerprints\' across the electromagnetic spectrum. These \'fingerprints\' are known as spectral signatures and enable identification of the materials that make up a scanned object. For example, having the spectral signature for oil helps mineralogists find new oil fields.</p>\r\n<p>Hyperspectral sensors collect information as a set of \'images\'. Each image represents a range of the electromagnetic spectrum and is also known as a spectral band. These \'images\' are then combined and form a three-dimensional hyperspectral data cube for processing and analysis.</p>\r\n<p>At our University, a collaboration with the chemistry department, on the analysis of painting masterworks (Van Gogh, Rembrandt, ...) involves sparse hyperspectral data. The aim is to use the latest in sparse data processing to create visual representations of the information.</p>');
